00:00:13.647 --> 00:00:22.489 position:19% line:89% align:start
[sounds of helicopter]

00:00:22.522 --> 00:00:24.424 position:10% line:89% align:start
MAN: Drake calling Somerset.

00:00:24.457 --> 00:00:26.426 position:33% line:5% align:start
Sleeping gas
injectors now attached

00:00:26.459 --> 00:00:28.762 position:24% line:5% align:start
to outer walls of
rooftop air conditioner.

00:00:28.795 --> 00:00:31.364 position:33% line:5% align:start
MAN: Roger.
Set it for 0220 hours.

00:00:31.398 --> 00:00:33.400 position:21% line:5% align:start
Wait for the signal.

00:01:15.142 --> 00:01:17.678 position:19% line:5% align:start
-You people are cops?

00:01:17.712 --> 00:01:20.514 position:13% line:5% align:start
Now I know there's no hope
for the justice system.

00:01:20.548 --> 00:01:23.150 position:13% line:83% align:start
-If you've got issues with
this world, change yourself.

00:01:23.184 --> 00:01:25.553 position:13% line:83% align:start
If that's a problem, block
your ears, shut your mouth,

00:01:25.586 --> 00:01:27.188 position:13% line:89% align:start
and go live like a hermit.

00:01:27.221 --> 00:01:29.423 position:13% line:89% align:start
And if that's a problem--

00:02:02.724 --> 00:02:03.725 position:38% line:89% align:start
[sirens]

00:02:19.574 --> 00:02:20.976 position:16% line:89% align:start
YAMAGUCHI: Another one?

00:02:21.009 --> 00:02:26.181 position:19% line:89% align:start
What's going on here?

00:02:26.214 --> 00:02:28.250 position:24% line:89% align:start
CHIEF: Yamaguchi.

00:02:28.283 --> 00:02:31.653 position:13% line:89% align:start
YAMAGUCHI: Oh, Chief Nibu.

00:02:31.687 --> 00:02:34.223 position:19% line:83% align:start
So what are you doing
down here after hours?

00:02:34.257 --> 00:02:35.157 position:24% line:89% align:start
[chief chuckling]

00:02:35.191 --> 00:02:36.892 position:13% line:89% align:start
CHIEF: Hell of a question.

00:02:36.925 --> 00:02:37.960 position:30% line:89% align:start
I was working.

00:02:37.993 --> 00:02:38.827 position:19% line:89% align:start
You know what that is.

00:02:38.860 --> 00:02:41.029 position:38% line:89% align:start
Working?

00:02:41.063 --> 00:02:42.831 position:7% line:83% align:start
Isn't that what you're doing?
-Yeah.

00:02:50.706 --> 00:02:51.941 position:13% line:89% align:start
CHIEF: How about a drink?

00:02:51.975 --> 00:02:54.110 position:27% line:89% align:start
Just you and me.

00:02:54.143 --> 00:02:57.113 position:35% line:83% align:start
-I can't.
Sorry.

00:03:08.057 --> 00:03:09.225 position:24% line:83% align:start
Think I'm going to
call it a night.

00:03:32.915 --> 00:03:38.155 position:27% line:89% align:start
[phone ringing]

00:03:38.188 --> 00:03:40.023 position:38% line:83% align:start
-Hello?
-Togusa.

00:03:40.056 --> 00:03:40.656 position:24% line:89% align:start
This is Yamaguchi.

00:03:40.690 --> 00:03:42.625 position:13% line:89% align:start
We worked together at HQ.

00:03:42.658 --> 00:03:43.826 position:27% line:89% align:start
You remember me?

00:03:43.860 --> 00:03:46.096 position:33% line:83% align:start
-Yamaguchi.
Oh, yeah.

00:03:46.130 --> 00:03:48.798 position:30% line:83% align:start
How you been?
It's been quite a long time.

00:03:48.831 --> 00:03:51.135 position:13% line:83% align:start
-Sorry to call you so late
out of the blue and all.

00:03:51.168 --> 00:03:52.835 position:24% line:83% align:start
But I'm analyzing
some sensitive data

00:03:52.870 --> 00:03:55.139 position:10% line:89% align:start
and I need a second opinion.

00:03:55.172 --> 00:03:56.173 position:19% line:89% align:start
Can I bring it to you?

00:03:56.206 --> 00:03:58.842 position:24% line:89% align:start
-Something happen?

00:03:58.876 --> 00:04:01.611 position:5% line:83% align:start
YAMAGUCHI (ON PHONE): Well, you
remember the Laughing Man case?

00:04:01.644 --> 00:04:03.047 position:24% line:89% align:start
-The Laughing Man?

00:04:03.080 --> 00:04:04.281 position:35% line:89% align:start
Oh, yeah.

00:04:04.314 --> 00:04:07.217 position:10% line:83% align:start
He was the guy who kidnapped
a CEO of a micro machine corp

00:04:07.251 --> 00:04:09.086 position:21% line:83% align:start
and had the nerve to
hold him for ransom.

00:04:09.119 --> 00:04:12.256 position:10% line:83% align:start
But that was six years ago.
YAMAGUCHI (ON PHONE): Right.

00:04:12.289 --> 00:04:14.358 position:16% line:83% align:start
I'm on the research unit
for that case right now,

00:04:14.391 --> 00:04:17.327 position:13% line:83% align:start
but some of our own people
are acting, well, suspicious.

00:04:17.361 --> 00:04:19.229 position:19% line:83% align:start
-You mean like a turf
war between detectives?

00:04:19.263 --> 00:04:22.032 position:13% line:83% align:start
YAMAGUCHI (ON PHONE): No.
It goes further up than that.

00:04:22.066 --> 00:04:24.101 position:7% line:89% align:start
Maybe all the way to the top.

00:04:24.134 --> 00:04:25.269 position:7% line:89% align:start
I'll tell you more when I see.

00:04:25.302 --> 00:04:26.603 position:5% line:89% align:start
I'll be there in about an hour.

00:04:26.637 --> 00:04:28.072 position:33% line:83% align:start
-All right.
I'll be waiting for you.

00:04:28.105 --> 00:04:29.807 position:16% line:83% align:start
I'll be waiting for you.
YAMAGUCHI (ON PHONE): Thanks.

00:04:31.775 --> 00:04:33.110 position:19% line:89% align:start
FEMALE VOICE: Togusa.

00:04:33.143 --> 00:04:34.611 position:24% line:83% align:start
We just got a call
from the chief.

00:04:34.645 --> 00:04:35.979 position:27% line:83% align:start
Meet up with the
team, A2 load out.

00:04:36.013 --> 00:04:37.014 position:30% line:89% align:start
TOGUSA: Roger.

00:04:50.929 --> 00:04:55.100 position:38% line:89% align:start
[sirens]

00:04:55.133 --> 00:04:56.901 position:24% line:89% align:start
[whistle blowing]

00:05:04.809 --> 00:05:06.744 position:24% line:83% align:start
-I can't hand over
command authority

00:05:06.778 --> 00:05:08.947 position:5% line:89% align:start
without a rational explanation.

00:05:08.980 --> 00:05:11.182 position:16% line:83% align:start
This matter falls within
police jurisdiction.

00:05:11.216 --> 00:05:13.651 position:7% line:89% align:start
-I'm not obligated to explain.

00:05:13.685 --> 00:05:14.986 position:24% line:89% align:start
Don't be stubborn.

00:05:15.019 --> 00:05:17.055 position:24% line:83% align:start
Relinquish command
authority to the military.

00:05:17.088 --> 00:05:20.125 position:27% line:89% align:start
-We're stubborn?

00:05:20.158 --> 00:05:22.227 position:10% line:83% align:start
ARAMAKI: Gentlemen, is this
any time for petty squabbles?

00:05:22.260 --> 00:05:25.130 position:35% line:89% align:start
-Aramaki.

00:05:30.802 --> 00:05:33.372 position:10% line:83% align:start
-Shouldn't our main concern
be the customers inside?

00:05:33.405 --> 00:05:35.174 position:35% line:89% align:start
-Yes, sir.

00:05:35.207 --> 00:05:38.042 position:5% line:83% align:start
We have reason to believe that
the minister of foreign affairs

00:05:38.077 --> 00:05:40.346 position:13% line:83% align:start
and his personal secretary
are among the clientele who

00:05:40.379 --> 00:05:42.414 position:19% line:83% align:start
are being held inside
the restaurant.

00:05:42.448 --> 00:05:44.984 position:10% line:83% align:start
It's been roughly 17 minutes
since geisha robots took

00:05:45.017 --> 00:05:47.386 position:21% line:83% align:start
the minister and the
other patrons hostage.

00:05:47.419 --> 00:05:50.289 position:19% line:83% align:start
-Have they issued any
claims or demands?

00:05:50.322 --> 00:05:51.423 position:5% line:89% align:start
OFFICER: Not at this time, sir.

00:05:51.457 --> 00:05:52.925 position:16% line:89% align:start
-Transmission blackout?

00:05:52.958 --> 00:05:54.426 position:21% line:89% align:start
-My guys are on it.

00:05:54.460 --> 00:05:56.762 position:21% line:89% align:start
-And media control?

00:05:56.795 --> 00:05:59.298 position:10% line:83% align:start
OFFICER: We put code 14 into
effect nine minutes ago.

00:05:59.331 --> 00:06:01.066 position:16% line:89% align:start
It won't hold for long.

00:06:01.100 --> 00:06:03.302 position:16% line:83% align:start
ARAMAKI: Section 9 will
handle the incident from here.

00:06:03.335 --> 00:06:04.703 position:21% line:89% align:start
Hold your positions.

00:06:04.737 --> 00:06:06.172 position:35% line:89% align:start
-Yes, sir.

00:06:06.205 --> 00:06:08.140 position:24% line:89% align:start
MALE VOICE: Major.

00:06:08.174 --> 00:06:10.442 position:27% line:83% align:start
The military is
itching to jump in.

00:06:10.476 --> 00:06:11.710 position:27% line:89% align:start
Watch your back.

00:06:11.744 --> 00:06:12.811 position:27% line:83% align:start
KUSANAGI: Thanks
for the concern.

00:06:12.845 --> 00:06:14.813 position:41% line:89% align:start
Batou.

00:06:14.847 --> 00:06:17.783 position:13% line:89% align:start
BATOU: I'm still on route.

00:06:17.816 --> 00:06:19.118 position:13% line:83% align:start
That explains the wiretap
I was getting when

00:06:19.151 --> 00:06:21.153 position:24% line:83% align:start
I was listening in
on the sniper team.

00:06:21.187 --> 00:06:22.489 position:24% line:83% align:start
KUSANAGI: Togusa.
Ishikawa.

00:06:25.392 --> 00:06:27.726 position:19% line:83% align:start
-Major, there are just
too many channels.

00:06:27.760 --> 00:06:30.162 position:16% line:83% align:start
This might take a couple
of hours to pinpoint.

00:06:30.197 --> 00:06:31.830 position:21% line:83% align:start
KUSANAGI: Togusa, go
to the main courtyard

00:06:31.864 --> 00:06:33.233 position:27% line:83% align:start
and get ready to
storm the place.

00:06:33.266 --> 00:06:34.301 position:33% line:89% align:start
-Copy that.

00:06:34.334 --> 00:06:37.404 position:27% line:89% align:start
KUSANAGI: Saito.

00:06:41.907 --> 00:06:43.276 position:16% line:83% align:start
SAITO: I've neutralized
the image curtain,

00:06:43.310 --> 00:06:46.279 position:16% line:83% align:start
but all those trees down
there limit my firing field.

00:06:46.313 --> 00:06:47.047 position:27% line:89% align:start
KUSANAGI: Pazu.

00:06:47.080 --> 00:06:49.416 position:41% line:89% align:start
Borma.

00:06:49.449 --> 00:06:50.383 position:13% line:89% align:start
PAZU: Ready when you are.

00:06:50.417 --> 00:06:51.784 position:21% line:83% align:start
KUSANAGI: Whoever's
controlling the geisha

00:06:51.817 --> 00:06:53.853 position:13% line:89% align:start
robots ought to be nearby.

00:06:53.887 --> 00:06:55.355 position:27% line:83% align:start
Don't shoot the
power transformer.

00:06:55.388 --> 00:06:58.258 position:13% line:83% align:start
I'll upload a virus before
he can wipe the evidence.

00:06:58.291 --> 00:07:00.493 position:19% line:83% align:start
PAZU: But Major, what
if the robot geishas

00:07:00.527 --> 00:07:01.962 position:21% line:89% align:start
demand a pay raise?

00:07:01.995 --> 00:07:03.863 position:21% line:89% align:start
BORMA: Knock it off.

00:07:03.897 --> 00:07:05.799 position:30% line:83% align:start
KUSANAGI: All
personnel in position.

00:07:05.832 --> 00:07:07.033 position:33% line:89% align:start
Standing by.

00:07:07.067 --> 00:07:08.134 position:38% line:89% align:start
-Right.

00:07:08.168 --> 00:07:09.402 position:38% line:83% align:start
Proceed.
KUSANAGI: Go.

00:07:53.180 --> 00:07:55.082 position:35% line:89% align:start
[creaking]

00:08:01.322 --> 00:08:02.323 position:35% line:89% align:start
[gunshot]

00:08:27.582 --> 00:08:28.450 position:21% line:89% align:start
-Togusa, look alive.

00:08:32.053 --> 00:08:34.256 position:10% line:83% align:start
Chief, the scene is secure.
ARAMAKI: Good.

00:08:34.289 --> 00:08:36.023 position:24% line:83% align:start
Bring the minister
and the others out.

00:08:36.058 --> 00:08:38.126 position:13% line:89% align:start
And be extremely careful.

00:08:38.160 --> 00:08:40.128 position:21% line:83% align:start
I have four vans and
a tent car, and all

00:08:40.162 --> 00:08:41.963 position:5% line:89% align:start
waiting for you at the entrance.

00:08:41.997 --> 00:08:44.132 position:27% line:83% align:start
Move them under
B6 guard protocol.

00:08:44.166 --> 00:08:51.273 position:5% line:89% align:start
[news reporter talking faintly]

00:08:57.212 --> 00:09:00.082 position:24% line:83% align:start
-Did Togusa spend
the whole night here?

00:09:00.115 --> 00:09:00.949 position:16% line:89% align:start
MAN: Uh, yeah, I guess.

00:09:00.982 --> 00:09:02.618 position:24% line:83% align:start
He said he had to
wait for someone.

00:09:09.692 --> 00:09:12.427 position:13% line:89% align:start
Hey, you're finally awake.

00:09:12.462 --> 00:09:14.162 position:13% line:89% align:start
TOGUSA: Highway accident.

00:09:14.196 --> 00:09:18.468 position:19% line:83% align:start
Police officer burned
beyond recognition.

00:09:18.501 --> 00:09:22.037 position:5% line:83% align:start
-Are you certain that the agent
who contacted you last night

00:09:22.070 --> 00:09:24.340 position:21% line:83% align:start
is the same one who
died in that accident?

00:09:24.374 --> 00:09:25.441 position:33% line:89% align:start
TOGUSA: Yes.

00:09:25.475 --> 00:09:27.909 position:10% line:83% align:start
He said there was suspicious
activity in his unit.

00:09:27.943 --> 00:09:30.179 position:16% line:83% align:start
He sounded very worried
to me at the time.

00:09:30.213 --> 00:09:32.914 position:13% line:83% align:start
-So you think his accident
wasn't an accident?

00:09:32.948 --> 00:09:34.117 position:27% line:83% align:start
TOGUSA: I don't
have any evidence,

00:09:34.150 --> 00:09:36.252 position:27% line:83% align:start
but the timing's
very convenient.

00:09:36.285 --> 00:09:38.354 position:7% line:89% align:start
-What did the lab report say?

00:09:38.388 --> 00:09:40.556 position:13% line:83% align:start
TOGUSA: They think he just
lost control of the car.

00:09:40.590 --> 00:09:43.159 position:27% line:89% align:start
Poor visibility.

00:09:43.192 --> 00:09:45.595 position:7% line:83% align:start
-Which is very possible, since
he was driving in a rainstorm.

00:09:45.628 --> 00:09:46.996 position:21% line:89% align:start
TOGUSA: Yeah, but--

00:09:47.029 --> 00:09:49.332 position:5% line:89% align:start
-Let him make his point, Major.

00:09:49.365 --> 00:09:52.034 position:16% line:83% align:start
Regardless of what might
have been the cause of death,

00:09:52.068 --> 00:09:53.703 position:30% line:83% align:start
this agent had
inside information

00:09:53.737 --> 00:09:55.338 position:10% line:89% align:start
that may be very pertinent.

00:09:55.371 --> 00:09:56.639 position:16% line:89% align:start
We need to follow it up.

00:09:56.672 --> 00:09:58.508 position:7% line:89% align:start
But we need to do it quietly.

00:09:58.541 --> 00:09:59.609 position:21% line:89% align:start
You have three days.

00:09:59.643 --> 00:10:00.510 position:19% line:89% align:start
Find out what you can.

00:10:00.543 --> 00:10:01.544 position:13% line:89% align:start
Thank you very much, sir.

00:10:10.554 --> 00:10:13.457 position:21% line:83% align:start
So we're back on the
Laughing Man case.

00:10:13.490 --> 00:10:14.525 position:24% line:89% align:start
What do you think?

00:10:14.558 --> 00:10:17.428 position:16% line:83% align:start
-I'd forgotten all about
it until he brought it up.

00:10:17.461 --> 00:10:20.564 position:5% line:83% align:start
Six years, and that same unit is
still working on the same case?

00:10:20.597 --> 00:10:22.965 position:21% line:83% align:start
-A lot of companies
were blackmailed,

00:10:22.999 --> 00:10:24.167 position:5% line:89% align:start
and they all have to be covered.

00:10:24.200 --> 00:10:26.537 position:21% line:83% align:start
It's the largest act
of corporate terrorism

00:10:26.570 --> 00:10:28.238 position:30% line:89% align:start
since the war.

00:10:28.272 --> 00:10:30.240 position:16% line:83% align:start
Even if they drop a case
without an indictment,

00:10:30.274 --> 00:10:33.143 position:24% line:83% align:start
HQ can't back away
because of public opinion.

00:10:33.177 --> 00:10:35.646 position:21% line:83% align:start
-I still say they're
taking their sweet time.

00:10:35.679 --> 00:10:36.880 position:21% line:89% align:start
-You've got a point.

00:10:36.914 --> 00:10:40.350 position:7% line:83% align:start
Even the top execs can't agree
on the culprit of the crime.

00:10:40.384 --> 00:10:43.287 position:13% line:83% align:start
Some say it's politically
motivated extremists who

00:10:43.320 --> 00:10:47.291 position:16% line:83% align:start
hate prosthetics and all
forms of cyber technology.

00:10:47.324 --> 00:10:50.461 position:13% line:83% align:start
Others think it's standard
corporate warfare--

00:10:50.494 --> 00:10:55.299 position:10% line:83% align:start
some conglomerate trying to
get an edge on the market.

00:10:55.332 --> 00:10:58.368 position:7% line:83% align:start
And still others believe it's
just about the ransom money.

00:10:58.402 --> 00:11:00.270 position:21% line:89% align:start
Plain old thievery.

00:11:00.304 --> 00:11:02.372 position:21% line:83% align:start
There are plenty of
theories, but no facts.

00:11:02.406 --> 00:11:04.508 position:16% line:83% align:start
They don't know if it's
one or a whole group.

00:11:04.542 --> 00:11:07.311 position:7% line:83% align:start
They don't know the suspect's
nationality, age, or sex.

00:11:07.344 --> 00:11:10.147 position:5% line:83% align:start
The only thing they agree on is
whoever broke into the system

00:11:10.180 --> 00:11:13.150 position:13% line:89% align:start
is a super class A hacker.

00:11:13.183 --> 00:11:15.587 position:21% line:83% align:start
-He was class A when
he started this thing.

00:11:15.620 --> 00:11:16.621 position:10% line:89% align:start
But he couldn't sustain it.

00:11:16.654 --> 00:11:19.324 position:13% line:89% align:start
His work turned mediocre.

00:11:19.357 --> 00:11:21.459 position:19% line:83% align:start
I don't like anything
about this case--

00:11:21.493 --> 00:11:24.462 position:21% line:83% align:start
not the hacker, the
corporations, or the cops.

00:11:24.496 --> 00:11:25.530 position:38% line:89% align:start
-Right.

00:11:25.563 --> 00:11:27.765 position:13% line:83% align:start
But we still have to check
out police headquarters.

00:11:27.799 --> 00:11:30.168 position:19% line:83% align:start
If there's high level
involvement in this,

00:11:30.201 --> 00:11:31.703 position:24% line:83% align:start
we have no choice
but to step in.

00:11:36.207 --> 00:11:38.276 position:35% line:89% align:start
[chanting]

00:11:49.087 --> 00:11:52.457 position:13% line:89% align:start
MRS. YAMAGUCH: Mr. Togusa?

00:11:52.490 --> 00:11:54.727 position:13% line:89% align:start
Thank you for coming here.

00:11:54.760 --> 00:11:56.060 position:21% line:89% align:start
I'm Mrs. Yamaguchi.

00:11:58.463 --> 00:11:59.364 position:33% line:89% align:start
-I'm sorry.

00:12:03.434 --> 00:12:06.572 position:7% line:89% align:start
But how did you know who I am?

00:12:06.605 --> 00:12:07.840 position:7% line:89% align:start
-My husband told me about you.

00:12:07.873 --> 00:12:10.476 position:13% line:89% align:start
He said I could trust you.

00:12:10.509 --> 00:12:12.545 position:21% line:83% align:start
I'm glad you came so
I could give you this.

00:12:12.578 --> 00:12:15.614 position:24% line:83% align:start
It arrived from my
husband this morning.

00:12:15.648 --> 00:12:18.784 position:21% line:83% align:start
He must have sent it
just before the accident.

00:12:18.817 --> 00:12:21.387 position:16% line:83% align:start
There was a note inside
saying to give it to you.

00:12:21.420 --> 00:12:23.489 position:24% line:83% align:start
He said you'd know
what to do with it.

