00:20:29.250 --> 00:20:31.751 position:16% line:83% align:start
two days earlier, but no
announcements were made

00:20:31.785 --> 00:20:34.654 position:27% line:83% align:start
in order to keep
the press at bay.

00:20:34.687 --> 00:20:37.291 position:16% line:83% align:start
This case was difficult
as hell, and investigators

00:20:37.324 --> 00:20:39.160 position:13% line:89% align:start
didn't find a single clue.

00:20:39.193 --> 00:20:43.330 position:7% line:83% align:start
Then, ironically, it suddenly
broke with that media stunt.

00:20:43.364 --> 00:20:47.301 position:7% line:83% align:start
This is where it all began-- a
theatrical crime widely known

00:20:47.334 --> 00:20:50.171 position:13% line:89% align:start
as Laughing Man Incident.

00:20:50.204 --> 00:20:52.973 position:5% line:83% align:start
According to the detectives who
worked on the case back then,

00:20:53.007 --> 00:20:56.043 position:21% line:83% align:start
Mr. Serano received
warnings prior to the event

00:20:56.077 --> 00:20:59.013 position:10% line:83% align:start
by word of mouth from people
that were close to him.

00:20:59.046 --> 00:21:01.682 position:16% line:83% align:start
But because their cyber
brains had been hacked,

00:21:01.715 --> 00:21:04.752 position:24% line:83% align:start
he didn't take the
situation seriously.

00:21:04.785 --> 00:21:06.654 position:24% line:83% align:start
Immediately after,
Serano himself

00:21:06.687 --> 00:21:09.190 position:21% line:83% align:start
was cyber hacked and
kidnapped from his home.

00:21:09.223 --> 00:21:12.760 position:19% line:83% align:start
An enormous ransom was
demanded for 10 billion yen

00:21:12.793 --> 00:21:15.029 position:21% line:83% align:start
and a hundred kilos
of gold bullion.

00:21:15.062 --> 00:21:18.632 position:16% line:83% align:start
Following that, however,
all contact was lost.

00:21:18.666 --> 00:21:20.901 position:21% line:83% align:start
Up until he appeared
on that TV broadcast,

00:21:20.935 --> 00:21:22.636 position:24% line:83% align:start
there had been no
inkling of news

00:21:22.670 --> 00:21:26.141 position:10% line:89% align:start
about Mr. Serano whatsoever.

00:21:26.174 --> 00:21:29.945 position:7% line:83% align:start
And while the Laughing Man was
threatening Serano on live TV,

00:21:29.978 --> 00:21:32.380 position:16% line:83% align:start
he took the opportunity
to plaster his logo

00:21:32.414 --> 00:21:35.683 position:16% line:83% align:start
over the camera's AI and
the eyes of onlookers,

00:21:35.716 --> 00:21:37.285 position:27% line:83% align:start
including those
of the TV station

00:21:37.319 --> 00:21:40.956 position:7% line:89% align:start
staff-- all done in real time.

00:21:40.989 --> 00:21:43.024 position:27% line:83% align:start
The Laughing Man
fled from police

00:21:43.058 --> 00:21:44.826 position:7% line:89% align:start
when they rushed to the scene.

00:21:44.860 --> 00:21:48.864 position:7% line:5% align:start
Yet, despite the fact that so
many people saw the suspect,

00:21:48.897 --> 00:21:51.366 position:19% line:83% align:start
the only ones who were
able to see his real face

00:21:51.399 --> 00:21:54.302 position:13% line:5% align:start
were two homeless men who
had not been cyberized.

00:21:54.336 --> 00:21:56.438 position:30% line:83% align:start
The reports of
those who testified

00:21:56.472 --> 00:21:58.773 position:21% line:83% align:start
seeing the Laughing
Man's face are famous.

00:21:58.807 --> 00:22:01.109 position:30% line:83% align:start
Based on these
eyewitness accounts,

00:22:01.143 --> 00:22:04.079 position:13% line:83% align:start
detectives came up with a
composite sketch of the logo

00:22:04.112 --> 00:22:05.847 position:33% line:89% align:start
every time.

00:22:05.881 --> 00:22:08.216 position:27% line:83% align:start
This bizarre and
disturbing incident,

00:22:08.250 --> 00:22:10.852 position:27% line:83% align:start
along with that
twisted pop icon,

00:22:10.886 --> 00:22:13.189 position:16% line:83% align:start
gained popularity among
a lot of young people

00:22:13.222 --> 00:22:15.158 position:10% line:89% align:start
and subculture commentators.

00:22:15.191 --> 00:22:17.326 position:30% line:83% align:start
At its peak of
popularity, the logo

00:22:17.360 --> 00:22:19.995 position:16% line:83% align:start
could be seen plastered
all over the city,

00:22:20.028 --> 00:22:22.998 position:7% line:83% align:start
and store shelves were filled
with branded merchandise.

00:22:23.032 --> 00:22:26.002 position:19% line:83% align:start
At the same time, acts
of corporate terrorism

00:22:26.035 --> 00:22:28.037 position:24% line:83% align:start
were occurring one
after the other,

00:22:28.070 --> 00:22:31.340 position:10% line:83% align:start
while the popularity of the
icon had even reached the point

00:22:31.374 --> 00:22:35.244 position:19% line:83% align:start
where it was featured
on TV programs.

00:22:35.278 --> 00:22:38.214 position:10% line:5% align:start
-Hot on the heels of Serano,
Japan Micro Industries

00:22:38.247 --> 00:22:41.350 position:5% line:5% align:start
has apparently been blackmailed
by the notorious Laughing Man.

00:22:41.384 --> 00:22:42.285 position:21% line:5% align:start
This is incredible.

00:22:42.318 --> 00:22:43.352 position:27% line:5% align:start
What are those?

00:22:43.386 --> 00:22:45.888 position:13% line:5% align:start
It looks like a warehouse
load of office desks?

00:22:45.922 --> 00:22:47.290 position:27% line:5% align:start
How in the world
were they all moved

00:22:47.323 --> 00:22:48.824 position:13% line:5% align:start
up here in a single night?

00:22:48.858 --> 00:22:50.793 position:24% line:5% align:start
The head office of
Sagawa Electronics

00:22:50.826 --> 00:22:52.461 position:21% line:5% align:start
has been blackmailed
this time, and I'm

00:22:52.495 --> 00:22:55.064 position:13% line:5% align:start
pretty sure this qualifies
as an unprecedented act

00:22:55.097 --> 00:22:56.766 position:16% line:5% align:start
of corporate terrorism.

00:22:56.799 --> 00:22:58.067 position:38% line:89% align:start
-Listen.

00:22:58.100 --> 00:23:00.002 position:21% line:89% align:start
The real one, right?

00:23:00.036 --> 00:23:03.773 position:33% line:83% align:start
-Please call
Nanoplant Industries.

00:23:03.806 --> 00:23:06.842 position:7% line:83% align:start
-Satsuma Meditech is the most
powerful corporation in Kyushu.

00:23:06.876 --> 00:23:07.743 position:27% line:89% align:start
Don't you know?

00:23:07.777 --> 00:23:09.812 position:21% line:83% align:start
Why would you go in
and plant a murder

00:23:09.845 --> 00:23:11.180 position:27% line:83% align:start
virus in there,
for heaven's sake?

00:23:11.215 --> 00:23:11.981 position:30% line:5% align:start
-I don't know.

00:23:12.014 --> 00:23:14.184 position:24% line:5% align:start
I imagine somebody
managed to hack

00:23:14.218 --> 00:23:16.253 position:21% line:5% align:start
into the landscaping
robots during the night.

00:23:16.286 --> 00:23:19.456 position:44% line:5% align:start
Go!
Look.

00:23:19.489 --> 00:23:20.257 position:35% line:5% align:start
It's him.

00:23:24.061 --> 00:23:25.861 position:27% line:83% align:start
-This MO matches
the threat against

00:23:25.895 --> 00:23:27.397 position:10% line:89% align:start
the superintendent-general.

00:23:27.431 --> 00:23:29.933 position:19% line:83% align:start
If this guy really did
all this by himself,

00:23:29.967 --> 00:23:31.902 position:24% line:83% align:start
he's definitely a
super class A hacker.

00:23:34.972 --> 00:23:37.908 position:10% line:83% align:start
But this timeworn kidnapping
case is beneath his abilities.

00:23:44.314 --> 00:23:46.316 position:21% line:83% align:start
KUSANAGI: After his
shocking and dramatic debut,

00:23:46.350 --> 00:23:48.385 position:19% line:83% align:start
he avoided the public
eye and went on

00:23:48.418 --> 00:23:51.021 position:27% line:83% align:start
to blackmail the
Serano Corporation.

00:23:51.054 --> 00:23:53.857 position:10% line:83% align:start
He did this by planting the
Virus Program Unto Death

00:23:53.890 --> 00:23:56.461 position:27% line:83% align:start
into their micro
machine production line.

00:23:56.494 --> 00:23:58.195 position:30% line:83% align:start
When sales of
their main chronic,

00:23:58.228 --> 00:24:01.064 position:16% line:83% align:start
medical micro machines,
drastically slowed

00:24:01.098 --> 00:24:03.934 position:16% line:83% align:start
and the price of Serano
stock took a nosedive,

00:24:03.967 --> 00:24:08.171 position:7% line:83% align:start
the blackmail quickly stopped,
as if that was the goal along.

00:24:08.205 --> 00:24:11.942 position:7% line:83% align:start
He then blackmailed six other
micro machine manufacturers,

00:24:11.975 --> 00:24:16.114 position:13% line:83% align:start
hitting one after another
using his unique method.

00:24:16.147 --> 00:24:18.583 position:24% line:83% align:start
This continued for
about three months.

00:24:18.616 --> 00:24:20.817 position:21% line:83% align:start
It sort of makes me
wonder if blackmail

00:24:20.851 --> 00:24:24.055 position:30% line:83% align:start
really was the
underlying motive.

00:24:24.088 --> 00:24:26.024 position:10% line:89% align:start
What was his true objective?

00:24:26.057 --> 00:24:28.259 position:21% line:83% align:start
Did he act alone, or
as part of a group?

00:24:28.293 --> 00:24:30.228 position:13% line:89% align:start
What's his race, his age?

00:24:30.261 --> 00:24:32.096 position:13% line:83% align:start
Is there something hidden
in his criminal philosophy?

00:24:35.199 --> 00:24:37.835 position:16% line:83% align:start
He left a hell of a lot
of unanswered riddles.

00:24:37.869 --> 00:24:40.405 position:30% line:83% align:start
Then, all of a
sudden, he vanished

00:24:40.438 --> 00:24:41.973 position:10% line:89% align:start
into the shadows of the net.

00:24:49.113 --> 00:24:51.382 position:5% line:83% align:start
-With regard to the announcement
of the news conference

00:24:51.416 --> 00:24:54.553 position:5% line:83% align:start
last night by the Laughing Man,
a terrorist who has resurfaced

00:24:54.586 --> 00:24:58.490 position:7% line:83% align:start
after six years, I consider it
to be an elaborate farce that

00:24:58.524 --> 00:25:01.092 position:19% line:83% align:start
was pulled off by the
Metropolitan Police.

00:25:01.125 --> 00:25:02.328 position:41% line:83% align:start
-Huh?
-Hold on.

00:25:02.361 --> 00:25:05.196 position:10% line:83% align:start
I'll admit that this threat
pushed the interceptor misuse

00:25:05.229 --> 00:25:06.964 position:27% line:83% align:start
matter clear out
of the limelight.

00:25:06.998 --> 00:25:09.368 position:16% line:83% align:start
But isn't your reasoning
a bit far fetched?

00:25:09.401 --> 00:25:11.069 position:27% line:89% align:start
I mean, come on.

00:25:11.102 --> 00:25:12.036 position:30% line:89% align:start
-Yeah, Chief.

00:25:12.070 --> 00:25:14.406 position:21% line:83% align:start
It's not like you to
make accusations rashly.

00:25:14.440 --> 00:25:16.408 position:30% line:83% align:start
Are you basing
this on something?

00:25:16.442 --> 00:25:17.343 position:41% line:83% align:start
-Mmhm.
Togusa.

00:25:17.376 --> 00:25:22.014 position:41% line:89% align:start
-Sir.

00:25:22.047 --> 00:25:23.982 position:24% line:89% align:start
ARAMAKI: Nanao Ei.

00:25:24.016 --> 00:25:26.952 position:16% line:83% align:start
He's a material witness
in the Laughing Man case.

00:25:26.985 --> 00:25:29.488 position:16% line:83% align:start
The Metro Police Special
Investigations Unit

00:25:29.521 --> 00:25:30.656 position:27% line:83% align:start
has had this man
under surveillance

00:25:30.689 --> 00:25:32.524 position:24% line:83% align:start
available for the
past three months.

00:25:32.558 --> 00:25:33.692 position:24% line:89% align:start
-Are you kidding?

00:25:33.726 --> 00:25:36.462 position:10% line:83% align:start
He seems like any run of the
mill office jockey to me.

00:25:36.495 --> 00:25:38.030 position:30% line:89% align:start
-Yeah, I know.

00:25:38.063 --> 00:25:40.632 position:21% line:83% align:start
That's certainly not
how I had imagined him.

00:25:40.666 --> 00:25:44.036 position:13% line:83% align:start
I figured the Laughing Man
would be a lot younger than him.

00:25:44.069 --> 00:25:45.471 position:24% line:83% align:start
ARAMAKI: According
to the SIU's records,

00:25:45.504 --> 00:25:47.539 position:21% line:83% align:start
he had been working
on event for Serano

00:25:47.574 --> 00:25:51.678 position:13% line:89% align:start
Genomics as a programmer.

00:25:51.711 --> 00:25:54.246 position:21% line:83% align:start
A year into the job,
though, a tip to the company

00:25:54.279 --> 00:25:58.451 position:21% line:83% align:start
exposed his activist
past, and he was let go.

00:25:58.485 --> 00:26:00.520 position:16% line:83% align:start
-Pretty straightforward
resume, Chief.

00:26:00.553 --> 00:26:01.654 position:41% line:89% align:start
-Yes.

00:26:01.688 --> 00:26:04.223 position:27% line:83% align:start
However, Special
Investigations HQ

00:26:04.256 --> 00:26:07.092 position:7% line:83% align:start
has suddenly started turning
up more circumstantial evidence

00:26:07.126 --> 00:26:09.995 position:16% line:83% align:start
that leads them to think
that Nanao is their man.

00:26:10.028 --> 00:26:11.698 position:27% line:83% align:start
-The SIU focused
its investigation

00:26:11.731 --> 00:26:14.134 position:19% line:83% align:start
on the grudge against
Serano angle this time.

00:26:14.167 --> 00:26:15.968 position:7% line:89% align:start
They're tailing him right now.

00:26:16.001 --> 00:26:18.171 position:16% line:83% align:start
And as soon as they link
Nanao to the threat,

00:26:18.204 --> 00:26:20.273 position:19% line:83% align:start
they're just going to
move in and arrest him.

00:26:20.306 --> 00:26:21.174 position:30% line:89% align:start
-Those idiots.

00:26:21.207 --> 00:26:23.143 position:24% line:83% align:start
There ain't no way
in hell that doofus

00:26:23.176 --> 00:26:24.544 position:13% line:89% align:start
could be the Laughing Man.

00:26:24.577 --> 00:26:26.713 position:19% line:83% align:start
That guys is battered
and deep-fried in guilt,

00:26:26.746 --> 00:26:28.114 position:21% line:89% align:start
he defines innocent.

00:26:28.148 --> 00:26:30.650 position:13% line:89% align:start
ARAMAKI: I agree with you.

00:26:30.683 --> 00:26:33.553 position:13% line:83% align:start
Why, then, would Special
Investigations swallow the bait

00:26:33.586 --> 00:26:35.188 position:27% line:83% align:start
when anyone else
can easily tell it's

00:26:35.221 --> 00:26:38.191 position:21% line:83% align:start
a decoy if they look
at the big picture?

00:26:38.224 --> 00:26:40.427 position:21% line:83% align:start
Besides, this whole
interceptor nonsense--

00:26:40.460 --> 00:26:42.295 position:24% line:83% align:start
there's something
we can't ignore.

00:26:42.328 --> 00:26:45.265 position:7% line:83% align:start
Don't forget police conspiracy
as a part of the equation,

00:26:45.298 --> 00:26:47.535 position:10% line:83% align:start
because it's still a theory
that's worth considering.

00:26:47.568 --> 00:26:51.070 position:10% line:83% align:start
-Well, since he-- Yamaguchi
was killed in the cross fire,

00:26:51.104 --> 00:26:53.072 position:35% line:89% align:start
probably.

00:26:53.106 --> 00:26:55.275 position:5% line:89% align:start
-I don't have any hard evidence.

00:26:55.308 --> 00:26:57.411 position:21% line:83% align:start
But if we can catch
Nanao Ei, who's

00:26:57.445 --> 00:26:59.580 position:19% line:83% align:start
been playing the role
of the Laughing Man

00:26:59.613 --> 00:27:02.416 position:10% line:83% align:start
and this elusive something
that's managed to fool the SIU,

00:27:02.450 --> 00:27:05.084 position:24% line:83% align:start
the answer should
surface on its own.

00:27:05.118 --> 00:27:07.688 position:21% line:83% align:start
We have two days to
find that something.

00:27:07.721 --> 00:27:09.088 position:35% line:89% align:start
-Oh, yeah.

00:27:09.122 --> 00:27:11.024 position:24% line:83% align:start
We sure uncorked a
big can of worms.

00:27:11.057 --> 00:27:12.293 position:38% line:89% align:start
-Right.

00:27:12.326 --> 00:27:15.162 position:5% line:83% align:start
You and Togusa, locate Nanao Ei
and start 24 hour surveillance.

00:27:15.196 --> 00:27:17.398 position:35% line:89% align:start
-Yes, sir.

00:27:17.431 --> 00:27:18.399 position:27% line:89% align:start
Don't screw up.

00:27:18.432 --> 00:27:20.568 position:19% line:83% align:start
TOGUSA: Don't you get
bored and wander off.

00:27:20.601 --> 00:27:22.670 position:13% line:83% align:start
ARAMAKI: The rest of you,
follow the major's instructions

00:27:22.703 --> 00:27:24.371 position:24% line:83% align:start
and find out who's
duping the SIU.

00:27:24.405 --> 00:27:28.209 position:30% line:89% align:start
ALL: Yes, sir.

00:27:28.242 --> 00:27:30.444 position:19% line:83% align:start
-So what is it, Major?
-Nothing.

00:27:42.256 --> 00:27:45.426 position:7% line:83% align:start
-Chief, I'm getting off of the
Nanao case as of this minute,

00:27:45.459 --> 00:27:48.028 position:16% line:83% align:start
and I could use the help
of Saito and Pazu as well.

00:27:48.062 --> 00:27:49.598 position:10% line:89% align:start
-What have you got in mind?

00:27:49.631 --> 00:27:52.199 position:27% line:83% align:start
-Protecting the
superintendent general.

00:27:52.233 --> 00:27:53.802 position:24% line:83% align:start
I think your hunch
was on the money,

00:27:53.835 --> 00:27:55.302 position:19% line:83% align:start
but I can't shake the
feeling that there's

00:27:55.336 --> 00:27:57.672 position:10% line:89% align:start
one piece which doesn't fit.

00:27:57.706 --> 00:27:59.508 position:21% line:83% align:start
My ghost is telling
me to tail Daido

00:27:59.541 --> 00:28:01.676 position:7% line:89% align:start
now to discover what that is.

00:28:01.710 --> 00:28:03.378 position:19% line:89% align:start
I hear it, whispering.

00:28:07.716 --> 00:28:09.083 position:33% line:89% align:start
-All right.

00:28:09.116 --> 00:28:10.519 position:5% line:89% align:start
You know what needs to be done.

00:28:10.552 --> 00:28:12.721 position:19% line:83% align:start
Every Section 9 member
has a unique ability,

00:28:12.754 --> 00:28:14.589 position:7% line:89% align:start
and you work best on your own.

00:28:14.623 --> 00:28:18.093 position:10% line:83% align:start
But individual success is a
reflection of strong teamwork.

00:28:18.126 --> 00:28:19.794 position:27% line:89% align:start
-Thanks, Chief.

00:28:19.828 --> 00:28:21.596 position:21% line:83% align:start
Put the word out to
Saito and Pazu, OK?

00:28:21.630 --> 00:28:28.570 position:24% line:89% align:start
ARAMAKI: It's me.

00:28:28.603 --> 00:28:31.273 position:19% line:89% align:start
What's Nanao's status?

00:28:31.306 --> 00:28:33.375 position:24% line:83% align:start
TOGUSA: No sign of
any activity yet.

00:28:33.408 --> 00:28:35.343 position:19% line:83% align:start
He's still sending out
emails sporadically.

00:28:41.651 --> 00:28:45.621 position:27% line:89% align:start
[phone ringing]

00:28:45.655 --> 00:28:47.355 position:41% line:89% align:start
-Yes?

00:28:47.389 --> 00:28:49.725 position:10% line:89% align:start
Thank you for all your help.

00:28:49.759 --> 00:28:53.361 position:7% line:83% align:start
that was only one of the plans
I had worked out in advance.

00:28:53.395 --> 00:28:54.664 position:33% line:89% align:start
Well, then.

00:28:54.697 --> 00:28:56.432 position:24% line:83% align:start
I hope you'll look
forward to it.

00:28:56.465 --> 00:28:57.633 position:41% line:89% align:start
Right.

00:28:57.667 --> 00:28:58.266 position:27% line:89% align:start
Good bye, then.

00:29:01.571 --> 00:29:03.204 position:24% line:89% align:start
No, it wasn't me.

00:29:03.239 --> 00:29:04.507 position:10% line:89% align:start
I didn't issue that warning.

00:29:04.540 --> 00:29:05.441 position:30% line:89% align:start
But no matter.

00:29:05.474 --> 00:29:07.677 position:24% line:83% align:start
That's because it
will all be over soon.

00:29:20.923 --> 00:29:22.792 position:24% line:77% align:start
SAITO: Major, the
Superindendent General has
entered the building.

00:29:22.825 --> 00:29:23.793 position:21% line:89% align:start
MAN: Routine check.

00:29:23.826 --> 00:29:24.760 position:10% line:89% align:start
Our man is in the building.

00:29:24.794 --> 00:29:27.597 position:21% line:83% align:start
KUSANAGI: Chief, how
are things on your end?

00:29:27.630 --> 00:29:28.731 position:24% line:89% align:start
ISHIKAWA: Got it.

00:29:28.764 --> 00:29:31.902 position:27% line:83% align:start
Like it says in
the SIU's report,

00:29:31.935 --> 00:29:34.370 position:19% line:83% align:start
Nanao's activities at
the time of each crime

00:29:34.403 --> 00:29:36.673 position:10% line:83% align:start
overwhelmingly substantiate
the possibility

00:29:36.707 --> 00:29:38.507 position:10% line:89% align:start
that he's the Laughing Man.

00:29:38.541 --> 00:29:41.377 position:10% line:83% align:start
But during my investigation
of those 43 related files,

00:29:41.410 --> 00:29:43.546 position:27% line:83% align:start
I came across a
lot of weird stuff

00:29:43.580 --> 00:29:46.482 position:10% line:83% align:start
in the testimonies of those
who knew the man back then.

00:29:46.516 --> 00:29:49.352 position:13% line:83% align:start
I noticed a definite trend
of admiration for Nanao.

00:29:49.385 --> 00:29:52.154 position:10% line:83% align:start
And I suspect this trend may
be the result of a forced

00:29:52.188 --> 00:29:54.290 position:7% line:5% align:start
language recognition program.

00:29:54.323 --> 00:29:57.327 position:16% line:83% align:start
These records have been
clearly manufactured--

00:29:57.361 --> 00:29:59.863 position:19% line:83% align:start
or rather, skillfully
overwritten.

00:29:59.896 --> 00:30:02.699 position:13% line:83% align:start
The cyber cops would never
have seen through these.

00:30:02.733 --> 00:30:04.635 position:30% line:83% align:start
Hell, not even
Special Investigations

00:30:04.668 --> 00:30:06.637 position:16% line:83% align:start
were able to tell these
were altered documents.

00:30:06.670 --> 00:30:09.239 position:21% line:83% align:start
This falsifying was
a quality forge job.

00:30:09.272 --> 00:30:10.674 position:30% line:89% align:start
-Superb work.

00:30:10.707 --> 00:30:11.742 position:21% line:89% align:start
Batou, do it quick.

00:30:11.775 --> 00:30:12.909 position:27% line:89% align:start
Apprehend Nanao.

00:30:12.943 --> 00:30:14.711 position:30% line:89% align:start
BATOU: Roger.

00:30:14.745 --> 00:30:17.914 position:5% line:83% align:start
ARAMAKI: There's a lot more to
this case than I ever imagined.

00:30:17.948 --> 00:30:19.650 position:19% line:89% align:start
KUSANAGI: Saito, Pazu.

00:30:19.683 --> 00:30:21.885 position:19% line:83% align:start
Is the police jamming
barrier causing

00:30:21.919 --> 00:30:23.955 position:5% line:83% align:start
interference in our connection?
SAITO: No.

00:30:23.988 --> 00:30:25.589 position:19% line:89% align:start
You're loud and clear.

00:30:25.622 --> 00:30:27.324 position:27% line:83% align:start
PAZU: Same here.
KUSANAGI: Really?

00:30:27.357 --> 00:30:28.458 position:21% line:89% align:start
MAN: Routine check.

00:30:28.492 --> 00:30:31.194 position:16% line:83% align:start
All personnel move from
security level beta to charlie.

00:30:31.228 --> 00:30:39.436 position:41% line:89% align:start
-Hey!

00:30:39.469 --> 00:30:40.705 position:16% line:83% align:start
Who are you people with?
BATOU: Move.

00:30:40.738 --> 00:30:41.471 position:27% line:89% align:start
Public security.

