-It's internal data from
a vocational aid center.

00:42:47.577 --> 00:42:49.111 position:7% line:89% align:start
TOGUSA: Vocational aid center?

00:42:49.145 --> 00:42:51.147 position:16% line:83% align:start
-They give job training
to some of their patients

00:42:51.180 --> 00:42:53.383 position:27% line:83% align:start
who have severe
Cyberbrain Closed Shell

00:42:53.417 --> 00:42:56.186 position:27% line:83% align:start
Syndrome to help
them reenter society.

00:42:56.219 --> 00:42:58.722 position:24% line:83% align:start
You have heard of
this, haven't you?

00:42:58.755 --> 00:43:01.224 position:7% line:83% align:start
-The database of the Ministry
of Health and Welfare

00:43:01.258 --> 00:43:02.726 position:7% line:89% align:start
was hacked into the last week.

00:43:02.759 --> 00:43:05.562 position:5% line:89% align:start
It was a large scale inside job.

00:43:05.595 --> 00:43:08.632 position:19% line:83% align:start
The leaked information
included material

00:43:08.665 --> 00:43:12.202 position:19% line:83% align:start
it was classified even
higher than A level.

00:43:12.235 --> 00:43:15.372 position:10% line:83% align:start
Notice the amount of time it
took to crack the barrier.

00:43:15.405 --> 00:43:18.074 position:10% line:83% align:start
They breached a triple layer
of varied attack barriers

00:43:18.108 --> 00:43:19.242 position:24% line:89% align:start
in just two hours.

00:43:19.276 --> 00:43:21.178 position:24% line:83% align:start
If it was only one
person, then they're

00:43:21.211 --> 00:43:24.181 position:19% line:83% align:start
an old pro who's even
better than the major.

00:43:24.214 --> 00:43:25.182 position:24% line:89% align:start
-Better than her?

00:43:25.215 --> 00:43:28.285 position:16% line:83% align:start
-Borma and Ishikawa did
a thorough route trace,

00:43:28.318 --> 00:43:31.321 position:19% line:83% align:start
and that building is
definitely the point of origin.

00:43:31.354 --> 00:43:33.423 position:21% line:83% align:start
However, the strange
thing is the circuits

00:43:33.457 --> 00:43:35.726 position:24% line:83% align:start
at the center are
normally kept isolated.

00:43:35.760 --> 00:43:37.495 position:24% line:83% align:start
That would make it
virtually impossible

00:43:37.528 --> 00:43:41.998 position:7% line:83% align:start
to establish external contact
from the inside and vice versa.

00:43:42.032 --> 00:43:43.568 position:16% line:83% align:start
-What's even more odd is
the Ministry of Health

00:43:43.601 --> 00:43:45.436 position:16% line:89% align:start
and Welfare's reaction.

00:43:45.470 --> 00:43:48.272 position:16% line:83% align:start
Someone's accessed their
highly classified data,

00:43:48.306 --> 00:43:50.608 position:19% line:83% align:start
but they haven't filed
a single damage report.

00:43:50.641 --> 00:43:52.610 position:24% line:83% align:start
Even if they were
embarrassed by the hacking,

00:43:52.643 --> 00:43:55.112 position:24% line:83% align:start
their response is
very unnatural.

00:43:55.146 --> 00:43:56.614 position:16% line:83% align:start
-They've got some stuff
in there that they

00:43:56.647 --> 00:43:58.382 position:10% line:89% align:start
don't want us to know about.

00:43:58.416 --> 00:44:01.052 position:7% line:83% align:start
But they can track us down if
we go about this the wrong way.

00:44:01.085 --> 00:44:02.053 position:24% line:89% align:start
-That's your part.

00:44:08.159 --> 00:44:10.361 position:30% line:83% align:start
TOGUSA: So, an
undercover investigation.

00:44:10.394 --> 00:44:12.563 position:13% line:83% align:start
Still tying up loose ends
in the Laughing Man case,

00:44:12.597 --> 00:44:15.199 position:21% line:83% align:start
and they send me out
on another assignment.

00:44:15.233 --> 00:44:16.367 position:7% line:89% align:start
What a bunch of slave drivers.

00:44:40.291 --> 00:44:42.661 position:24% line:89% align:start
[swing squeaking]

00:45:38.484 --> 00:45:40.787 position:13% line:83% align:start
-Some cases of Cyberbrain
Closed Shell Syndrome

00:45:40.820 --> 00:45:45.123 position:7% line:83% align:start
involve complications that can
lead to intellectual damage.

00:45:45.157 --> 00:45:46.426 position:21% line:83% align:start
But there are quite
a few patients

00:45:46.459 --> 00:45:48.595 position:16% line:83% align:start
who display a surprising
knack for cyberspace.

00:45:52.799 --> 00:45:56.235 position:5% line:83% align:start
We make use of the peculiarities
of their condition in their job

00:45:56.269 --> 00:46:00.506 position:13% line:83% align:start
training by having these
children program barrier mazes.

00:46:00.540 --> 00:46:03.509 position:21% line:83% align:start
Occasionally, these
activities result in a barrier

00:46:03.543 --> 00:46:06.713 position:24% line:83% align:start
so remarkable that
government agencies adopt it.

00:46:06.746 --> 00:46:07.881 position:30% line:83% align:start
Each and every
one is constructed

00:46:07.915 --> 00:46:10.683 position:13% line:89% align:start
in a truly unique fashion.

00:46:10.717 --> 00:46:14.320 position:5% line:83% align:start
I'm certain if we were to leave
them alone, they would go on,

00:46:14.354 --> 00:46:16.824 position:19% line:83% align:start
never stopping, never
bored, assembling

00:46:16.857 --> 00:46:17.624 position:13% line:89% align:start
and dismantling barriers.

00:46:29.937 --> 00:46:31.839 position:27% line:83% align:start
I'll put you in
charge of a relatively

00:46:31.872 --> 00:46:34.408 position:5% line:89% align:start
manageable single group for now.

00:46:34.441 --> 00:46:36.810 position:21% line:89% align:start
Togusa, this is Aoi.

00:46:36.844 --> 00:46:38.412 position:13% line:89% align:start
He's one of your charges.

00:46:38.445 --> 00:46:39.546 position:38% line:89% align:start
-Right.

00:46:39.580 --> 00:46:41.280 position:7% line:83% align:start
-I believe the other children
are back in their room,

00:46:41.315 --> 00:46:43.350 position:13% line:89% align:start
so take him to join them.

00:46:43.384 --> 00:46:44.284 position:33% line:89% align:start
-Yes, ma'am.

00:46:49.723 --> 00:46:50.858 position:33% line:89% align:start
-Aoi, right?

00:46:50.891 --> 00:46:51.792 position:27% line:89% align:start
Nice to meet ya.

00:47:05.472 --> 00:47:06.774 position:30% line:89% align:start
-Christ, Aoi.

00:47:06.807 --> 00:47:08.509 position:24% line:89% align:start
What took you so--

00:47:08.542 --> 00:47:09.410 position:44% line:89% align:start
-Hi.

00:47:09.443 --> 00:47:10.377 position:33% line:89% align:start
I'm Togusa.

00:47:10.411 --> 00:47:13.681 position:19% line:89% align:start
I'm taking over today.

00:47:13.714 --> 00:47:14.415 position:21% line:89% align:start
How you doing there?

00:47:23.825 --> 00:47:24.993 position:27% line:83% align:start
Hey, you want to
play a game of catch?

00:47:25.026 --> 00:47:25.694 position:41% line:89% align:start
-Hey!

00:47:25.727 --> 00:47:26.828 position:30% line:89% align:start
Give it back!

00:47:26.861 --> 00:47:28.262 position:13% line:89% align:start
-He's getting freaked out.

00:47:28.295 --> 00:47:32.634 position:44% line:89% align:start
-Oh.

00:47:40.775 --> 00:47:44.312 position:7% line:83% align:start
-He-- he goes into panic mode
when he doesn't have his mitt.

00:47:44.345 --> 00:47:46.881 position:27% line:83% align:start
Besides, nobody
wants to go outside.

00:47:46.915 --> 00:47:52.787 position:33% line:89% align:start
Not anymore.

00:47:52.821 --> 00:47:56.491 position:19% line:83% align:start
-Hey, the chief swears
he's gonna come again!

00:47:56.524 --> 00:47:57.093 position:41% line:89% align:start
-Huh?

00:47:57.126 --> 00:47:58.927 position:30% line:83% align:start
-You mean it?
-Mmhm.

00:47:58.960 --> 00:48:00.462 position:13% line:89% align:start
I heard about it just now.

00:48:00.495 --> 00:48:01.429 position:38% line:89% align:start
-No way!

00:48:01.463 --> 00:48:02.932 position:10% line:89% align:start
He was here just last week.

00:48:02.965 --> 00:48:05.868 position:33% line:89% align:start
-Last week?

00:48:05.901 --> 00:48:07.736 position:16% line:89% align:start
So who's this chief guy?

00:48:07.769 --> 00:48:10.371 position:24% line:83% align:start
-Hey, pretty slick
of you, mister.

00:48:10.405 --> 00:48:11.740 position:41% line:89% align:start
-Shh.

00:48:11.774 --> 00:48:13.541 position:30% line:89% align:start
-What's wrong?

00:48:13.575 --> 00:48:15.978 position:16% line:83% align:start
-We don't trust grownups
around here, especially ones

00:48:16.011 --> 00:48:17.813 position:24% line:89% align:start
we don't know yet.

00:48:17.847 --> 00:48:19.581 position:30% line:89% align:start
BOY: Oh, yeah.

00:48:19.615 --> 00:48:22.383 position:7% line:83% align:start
BOY: So don't think that we'll
just blab everything to you.

00:48:22.417 --> 00:48:23.719 position:19% line:89% align:start
-That's pretty strict.

00:48:23.753 --> 00:48:24.920 position:27% line:89% align:start
-We have to be.

00:48:24.954 --> 00:48:27.656 position:24% line:83% align:start
-Hey, I'm gonna go
tell the others, OK?

00:48:27.690 --> 00:48:34.362 position:33% line:89% align:start
-Yeah, sure.

00:48:34.396 --> 00:48:35.164 position:35% line:89% align:start
-Comrades!

00:48:35.197 --> 00:48:37.366 position:27% line:83% align:start
Word has it that
starting tomorrow,

00:48:37.399 --> 00:48:40.536 position:7% line:83% align:start
we'll be going back to the lab
to participate in simulations.

00:48:40.569 --> 00:48:41.504 position:24% line:89% align:start
-Oh, simulations!

00:48:41.537 --> 00:48:46.475 position:33% line:89% align:start
[chattering]

00:48:46.509 --> 00:48:49.645 position:21% line:83% align:start
-They say that what
we've acquired in secret

00:48:49.678 --> 00:48:54.650 position:10% line:83% align:start
might help the investigation
of the Laughing Man case.

00:48:54.683 --> 00:48:57.953 position:7% line:83% align:start
-Does this have to do with the
natural oil we used to get?

00:48:57.988 --> 00:48:59.222 position:13% line:89% align:start
-I don't know about that.

00:48:59.256 --> 00:49:02.959 position:5% line:83% align:start
But the day has finally arrived
when we can contribute mentally

00:49:02.993 --> 00:49:05.461 position:19% line:83% align:start
as well as physically
to Section 9.

00:49:05.494 --> 00:49:07.496 position:13% line:89% align:start
-That's a huge promotion.

00:49:07.530 --> 00:49:09.732 position:7% line:83% align:start
-Uh, what is it we're supposed
to have acquired again?

00:49:09.766 --> 00:49:11.400 position:27% line:89% align:start
-Individuality!

00:49:11.433 --> 00:49:13.837 position:24% line:83% align:start
Little by little,
our AIs have begun

00:49:13.870 --> 00:49:15.638 position:19% line:83% align:start
to develop individual
differences.

00:49:15.672 --> 00:49:16.873 position:41% line:89% align:start
-Yeah.

00:49:16.907 --> 00:49:18.909 position:13% line:83% align:start
Even though we synchronize
our data after every mission.

00:49:18.942 --> 00:49:20.043 position:33% line:89% align:start
-Weird, huh?

00:49:20.076 --> 00:49:21.477 position:24% line:83% align:start
-It's the opposite
of what happened

00:49:21.510 --> 00:49:23.713 position:21% line:83% align:start
with those Laughing
Man copycats.

00:49:23.747 --> 00:49:26.983 position:16% line:83% align:start
-But it's also possible
they'll just have us scrapped.

00:49:27.017 --> 00:49:28.118 position:41% line:89% align:start
-What?

00:49:28.151 --> 00:49:29.986 position:10% line:89% align:start
-What's with the negativity?

00:49:30.020 --> 00:49:32.823 position:19% line:83% align:start
-If there are new jobs
waiting for us at the lab,

00:49:32.856 --> 00:49:33.723 position:24% line:83% align:start
then doesn't that
mean we've been

00:49:33.757 --> 00:49:35.859 position:24% line:83% align:start
declared unfit for
our current duties?

00:49:35.892 --> 00:49:38.728 position:10% line:83% align:start
Though I still like the idea
of us contributing mentally.

00:49:38.762 --> 00:49:41.398 position:24% line:83% align:start
To take an extreme
theoretical example,

00:49:41.431 --> 00:49:42.566 position:21% line:83% align:start
it's not beyond the
realm of possibility

00:49:42.599 --> 00:49:45.635 position:10% line:83% align:start
that a mass of data with no
body could carry a ghost.

00:49:45.669 --> 00:49:46.603 position:27% line:89% align:start
TACHIKOMA: Whoa.

00:49:46.636 --> 00:49:47.637 position:19% line:89% align:start
You came up with that?

00:49:47.671 --> 00:49:49.906 position:30% line:89% align:start
I'm impressed.

00:49:49.940 --> 00:49:51.775 position:24% line:83% align:start
Why don't you join
their conversation?

00:49:51.808 --> 00:49:54.544 position:16% line:83% align:start
-No, I'm more interested
in books lately.

00:49:54.578 --> 00:49:57.914 position:38% line:83% align:start
-Really?
What you reading?

00:49:57.949 --> 00:50:00.117 position:16% line:89% align:start
-"Flowers For Algernon."

00:50:00.151 --> 00:50:01.518 position:24% line:83% align:start
-Wow, you're going
to the trouble

00:50:01.551 --> 00:50:02.920 position:7% line:89% align:start
of reading it on paper medium?

00:50:02.954 --> 00:50:06.090 position:16% line:83% align:start
-Whether it's a mere job
rotation or impending

00:50:06.123 --> 00:50:09.026 position:10% line:83% align:start
destruction, I don't want to
forget my love of reading.

00:50:13.030 --> 00:50:13.965 position:24% line:89% align:start
BATOU: Tachikoma.

00:50:13.998 --> 00:50:16.167 position:27% line:89% align:start
-Oh, Mr. Batou.

00:50:16.200 --> 00:50:17.500 position:21% line:83% align:start
-Why don't you come
with me for a while

00:50:17.534 --> 00:50:19.136 position:24% line:83% align:start
and give me a hand
doing some target

00:50:19.170 --> 00:50:21.138 position:10% line:89% align:start
practice with the trainees?

00:50:21.172 --> 00:50:24.508 position:38% line:89% align:start
-Coming!

00:50:24.542 --> 00:50:26.043 position:21% line:83% align:start
-Now, what were you
guys talking about?

00:50:26.077 --> 00:50:28.411 position:30% line:89% align:start
-Oh, nothing.

00:50:28.446 --> 00:50:30.681 position:16% line:83% align:start
Anyway, what am I gonna
do with you now, Batou?

00:50:30.715 --> 00:50:34.051 position:16% line:83% align:start
You can't handle target
practice without me.

00:50:34.085 --> 00:50:35.086 position:21% line:89% align:start
BATOU: I guess not.

00:50:35.119 --> 00:50:37.889 position:7% line:89% align:start
-Why does he always get to go?

00:50:37.922 --> 00:50:39.657 position:10% line:83% align:start
TACHIKOMA: Maybe we need to
find out the real reason why

00:50:39.690 --> 00:50:41.626 position:21% line:83% align:start
the Major is sending
us back to the lab.

00:50:51.602 --> 00:50:52.837 position:33% line:89% align:start
-What's up?

00:50:52.870 --> 00:50:55.940 position:24% line:83% align:start
Why'd you want me
to meet you here?

00:50:55.974 --> 00:50:59.644 position:5% line:83% align:start
I'm guessing it's not to confess
your burning passion for me.

00:50:59.677 --> 00:51:01.213 position:21% line:83% align:start
-It's the only room
in the building that's

00:51:01.246 --> 00:51:03.882 position:10% line:83% align:start
electromagnetically shielded
so we can have some privacy.

00:51:10.956 --> 00:51:13.225 position:10% line:89% align:start
-Pass that dossier to Batou.

00:51:17.829 --> 00:51:20.132 position:21% line:83% align:start
-Just glance through
it, all right?

00:51:20.165 --> 00:51:22.200 position:33% line:89% align:start
You spot it?

00:51:22.234 --> 00:51:23.602 position:10% line:89% align:start
KUSANAGI: Don't turnaround.

00:51:23.635 --> 00:51:25.203 position:30% line:83% align:start
But there's a
camouflaged Tachikoma

00:51:25.237 --> 00:51:26.638 position:27% line:83% align:start
hanging from the
corridor ceiling.

00:51:33.211 --> 00:51:34.513 position:19% line:89% align:start
It's reading our lips.

00:51:34.546 --> 00:51:36.615 position:10% line:89% align:start
Pretend you haven't noticed.

00:51:36.648 --> 00:51:38.750 position:19% line:83% align:start
We'll physically speak
about something else

00:51:38.784 --> 00:51:40.986 position:21% line:83% align:start
while we're talking
via encrypted cybercom.

00:51:41.019 --> 00:51:42.487 position:19% line:89% align:start
BATOU: What the hell?

00:51:42.521 --> 00:51:43.855 position:5% line:89% align:start
Why go through all this trouble?

00:51:46.692 --> 00:51:48.660 position:10% line:89% align:start
TACHIKOMA: Now, what's this?

00:51:48.694 --> 00:51:50.562 position:27% line:83% align:start
Well, to make a
long story short,

00:51:50.595 --> 00:51:51.830 position:27% line:83% align:start
judging from the
end results, there

00:51:51.863 --> 00:51:54.633 position:13% line:83% align:start
are major issues regarding
your qualifications

00:51:54.666 --> 00:51:56.635 position:13% line:89% align:start
as a training instructor.

00:51:56.668 --> 00:51:58.071 position:16% line:83% align:start
KUSANAGI: Well, to make
a long story short,

00:51:58.104 --> 00:52:00.539 position:19% line:83% align:start
I have a serious issue
with the similarities

00:52:00.572 --> 00:52:02.141 position:33% line:83% align:start
between the
Tachikomas' development

00:52:02.175 --> 00:52:03.843 position:13% line:89% align:start
and the Laughing Man case.

00:52:03.876 --> 00:52:06.179 position:16% line:83% align:start
Their formation of egos,
which should be impossible,

00:52:06.212 --> 00:52:08.714 position:27% line:83% align:start
and the loss of
individuality-- at first, these

00:52:08.748 --> 00:52:10.783 position:35% line:83% align:start
seem to be
contradictory problems,

00:52:10.817 --> 00:52:12.719 position:21% line:83% align:start
but we need to keep
a close eye on them

00:52:12.752 --> 00:52:16.689 position:7% line:83% align:start
as unintended consequences of
information synchronization.

00:52:16.723 --> 00:52:18.791 position:7% line:83% align:start
BATOU: Hey, I don't feed them
natural oil on the sly anymore.

00:52:18.825 --> 00:52:21.160 position:13% line:83% align:start
KUSANAGI: No one suspects
you of doing that.

00:52:21.194 --> 00:52:22.161 position:24% line:83% align:start
I wouldn't have a
problem with this

00:52:22.195 --> 00:52:24.931 position:16% line:83% align:start
if it had happened in a
lab, but for a weapon,

00:52:24.964 --> 00:52:25.631 position:21% line:89% align:start
it could be lethal.

00:52:28.768 --> 00:52:31.604 position:5% line:83% align:start
TACHIKOMA: Hey, I'm not beating
them up on the sly anymore.

00:52:31.637 --> 00:52:33.906 position:27% line:83% align:start
No one suspects
you of doing that.

00:52:33.940 --> 00:52:35.108 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh.

00:52:35.141 --> 00:52:37.944 position:10% line:83% align:start
It doesn't look like they're
talking about us after all.

00:52:37.977 --> 00:52:39.313 position:21% line:83% align:start
-Don't we still have
the option of doing

00:52:39.346 --> 00:52:42.548 position:19% line:83% align:start
a full initialization
of their AI?

00:52:42.582 --> 00:52:46.019 position:13% line:83% align:start
-We tried that, but we got
the exact same results.

00:52:46.052 --> 00:52:50.690 position:10% line:83% align:start
I'm sorry, but all Tachikoma
use is suspended as of today.

00:52:50.723 --> 00:52:52.859 position:16% line:83% align:start
On the brighter side, it
looks like their AI will

00:52:52.892 --> 00:52:57.031 position:5% line:83% align:start
be useful in running simulations
on the Laughing Man copycats.

00:52:57.064 --> 00:52:59.266 position:16% line:83% align:start
They won't be told, but
after they've been disarmed,

00:52:59.299 --> 00:53:00.934 position:19% line:83% align:start
we'll send them to the
test lab, where they'll

00:53:00.968 --> 00:53:03.569 position:30% line:83% align:start
assist us with
our investigation.

00:53:03.603 --> 00:53:04.604 position:30% line:89% align:start
Is that clear?

00:53:09.076 --> 00:53:12.046 position:19% line:83% align:start
-Are you giving me an
order as my superior?

00:53:12.079 --> 00:53:14.048 position:27% line:89% align:start
KUSANAGI: I am.

00:53:14.081 --> 00:53:17.051 position:16% line:83% align:start
-I don't have the luxury
of refusing, do I?

00:53:17.084 --> 00:53:20.054 position:33% line:89% align:start
I'll comply.

00:53:20.087 --> 00:53:21.188 position:30% line:83% align:start
KUSANAGI: It's
time to reestablish

00:53:21.221 --> 00:53:22.623 position:21% line:89% align:start
contact with Togusa.

00:53:22.656 --> 00:53:24.758 position:24% line:83% align:start
We'll go there the
old-fashioned way.

00:53:24.792 --> 00:53:25.759 position:33% line:89% align:start
BATOU: What?

00:53:25.793 --> 00:53:28.095 position:19% line:83% align:start
I don't even have time
to say goodbye to them?

00:53:28.128 --> 00:53:30.164 position:30% line:83% align:start
TOGUSA: Sorry.
But I'm afraid not.

00:53:38.205 --> 00:53:41.075 position:5% line:83% align:start
TOGUSA: If somebody is using the
barriers created by these kids,

00:53:41.108 --> 00:53:43.710 position:13% line:83% align:start
it might explain why that
hacking of the Ministry

00:53:43.744 --> 00:53:46.281 position:19% line:83% align:start
of Health and Welfare
was so skillful.

00:53:46.314 --> 00:53:47.714 position:38% line:89% align:start
-I see.

00:53:47.748 --> 00:53:49.683 position:21% line:83% align:start
Any suspects so far?
TOGUSA: No.

00:53:49.716 --> 00:53:52.753 position:38% line:83% align:start
Not yet.
But this is one weird operation.

00:53:52.786 --> 00:53:54.389 position:27% line:83% align:start
They've even got
a heavy load-out

00:53:54.422 --> 00:53:56.224 position:13% line:89% align:start
cyborg stalking the halls.

00:53:56.257 --> 00:53:57.624 position:33% line:89% align:start
-Copy that.

00:53:57.658 --> 00:53:59.027 position:30% line:83% align:start
Carry on your
investigation for now.

00:53:59.060 --> 00:53:59.726 position:30% line:89% align:start
TOGUSA: Roger.

00:53:59.760 --> 00:54:02.263 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:54:07.869 --> 00:54:10.805 position:16% line:83% align:start
So, somebody besides me
has been using this, huh?

00:54:14.342 --> 00:54:17.378 position:24% line:83% align:start
I thought what I'd
do was I'd pretend

00:54:17.412 --> 00:54:23.751 position:24% line:83% align:start
I was one of those
deaf-mutes, or should I?

00:54:23.785 --> 00:54:24.686 position:30% line:89% align:start
What the hell?

00:54:31.159 --> 00:54:31.893 position:35% line:89% align:start
Oil paint.

00:54:36.965 --> 00:54:38.867 position:13% line:83% align:start
-You're in charge for now.
-Right.

00:54:38.900 --> 00:54:42.204 position:35% line:89% align:start
-It's you.

00:54:42.238 --> 00:54:43.272 position:41% line:89% align:start
Hello.

00:54:43.305 --> 00:54:46.175 position:27% line:89% align:start
-Good afternoon.

00:54:46.208 --> 00:54:47.276 position:24% line:89% align:start
Going out, ma'am?

00:54:47.309 --> 00:54:48.710 position:41% line:89% align:start
-Yes.

00:54:48.743 --> 00:54:50.246 position:24% line:83% align:start
There's a welfare
industry gathering.

00:54:50.279 --> 00:54:51.779 position:33% line:83% align:start
-Oh, really?
Have fun.

00:55:07.296 --> 00:55:09.365 position:35% line:89% align:start
Wait here.

00:55:09.398 --> 00:55:11.834 position:13% line:83% align:start
Sorry about this, but I'll
be done in a minute, OK?

00:55:14.970 --> 00:55:17.106 position:44% line:83% align:start
Hm.
Huh?

00:55:25.415 --> 00:55:27.783 position:30% line:83% align:start
No suspicious
records to speak of,

00:55:27.816 --> 00:55:29.985 position:24% line:83% align:start
and zero visitors
last week, huh?

00:55:34.424 --> 00:55:35.925 position:38% line:89% align:start
Dammit.

00:55:35.958 --> 00:55:37.494 position:24% line:83% align:start
Not being able to
access external memory

00:55:37.527 --> 00:55:38.261 position:21% line:89% align:start
is a friggin' pain.

00:55:43.133 --> 00:55:46.203 position:19% line:89% align:start
WOMAN: Dear, oh, dear.

00:55:46.236 --> 00:55:50.806 position:10% line:83% align:start
You've abandoned your charge
to do a bit of spying?

00:55:50.839 --> 00:55:51.874 position:21% line:89% align:start
Search all you want.

00:55:51.907 --> 00:55:55.011 position:16% line:83% align:start
You won't find any clues
about the chief in there.

00:55:55.045 --> 00:55:57.214 position:19% line:83% align:start
-I guess you're in no
mood for excuses, right?

00:56:00.917 --> 00:56:02.485 position:24% line:83% align:start
-You can hurt him,
but don't kill him.

00:56:02.519 --> 00:56:03.420 position:33% line:89% align:start
-Yes, ma'am.

00:56:03.453 --> 00:56:06.022 position:21% line:89% align:start
-Now, wait a minute.

00:56:06.056 --> 00:56:09.025 position:21% line:83% align:start
If we fight in here,
your paintings could be--

00:56:09.059 --> 00:56:10.260 position:21% line:83% align:start
-Is that what you're
going to fight with?

00:56:10.293 --> 00:56:11.161 position:41% line:89% align:start
-Uh--

00:56:23.173 --> 00:56:26.042 position:21% line:83% align:start
-Painting shouldn't
be treated roughly.

00:56:32.283 --> 00:56:36.786 position:10% line:83% align:start
Unlike electronic data, they
can't be duplicated, dumbass.

00:56:52.570 --> 00:56:54.105 position:24% line:83% align:start
Didn't think I was
armed, did you?

00:57:25.169 --> 00:57:25.836 position:33% line:89% align:start
-Section 9.

00:57:34.078 --> 00:57:35.913 position:13% line:89% align:start
-Major, unusual activity.

00:57:35.946 --> 00:57:39.083 position:19% line:83% align:start
Every terminal in the
center just went online.

00:57:39.116 --> 00:57:42.487 position:19% line:89% align:start
-Something's happened.

00:57:42.521 --> 00:57:44.122 position:16% line:89% align:start
-It's our access codes.

00:57:44.156 --> 00:57:45.624 position:24% line:83% align:start
They're attempting
to decrypt them.

00:57:45.657 --> 00:57:47.292 position:19% line:89% align:start
-Was his cover blown?

00:57:47.326 --> 00:57:48.593 position:30% line:89% align:start
-I don't know.

00:57:48.627 --> 00:57:49.294 position:24% line:89% align:start
Cut all circuits.

00:57:49.328 --> 00:57:51.363 position:41% line:89% align:start
Hurry.

00:57:51.396 --> 00:57:52.597 position:21% line:89% align:start
What's the hold up?

00:57:52.631 --> 00:57:54.199 position:21% line:89% align:start
-I-- I'm locked out.

00:57:54.232 --> 00:57:57.469 position:33% line:89% align:start
-Batou, now!

00:57:57.502 --> 00:57:59.037 position:13% line:89% align:start
We're pulling Togusa out.

00:57:59.071 --> 00:58:00.072 position:44% line:89% align:start
-OK.

00:58:00.105 --> 00:58:02.007 position:21% line:83% align:start
KUSANAGI: Ishikawa,
commandeer their circuits.

00:58:02.040 --> 00:58:03.375 position:10% line:89% align:start
Seito, find the back route.

00:58:13.619 --> 00:58:14.554 position:35% line:89% align:start
-Got him!

00:58:14.587 --> 00:58:17.590 position:7% line:89% align:start
Man, did I fly that AI peeper.

00:58:17.623 --> 00:58:19.257 position:30% line:89% align:start
CHIEF: Garoha.

00:58:19.291 --> 00:58:20.258 position:27% line:89% align:start
-Hey, what's up?

00:58:20.292 --> 00:58:22.928 position:10% line:89% align:start
Where have you been, chief?

00:58:22.961 --> 00:58:24.129 position:7% line:89% align:start
CHIEF: Things have gotten bad.

00:58:24.162 --> 00:58:26.098 position:27% line:83% align:start
I was spotted by
people on the outside.

00:58:26.131 --> 00:58:29.201 position:27% line:83% align:start
A lot of adults
will be coming soon.

00:58:29.234 --> 00:58:32.305 position:7% line:89% align:start
I'm disappearing before then.

00:58:32.338 --> 00:58:34.005 position:41% line:89% align:start
-Why?

00:58:34.039 --> 00:58:35.575 position:19% line:83% align:start
Till now, everything's
been going smoothly.

00:58:35.608 --> 00:58:38.311 position:24% line:83% align:start
We'll protect you,
Chief, same as always.

00:58:38.344 --> 00:58:39.178 position:44% line:89% align:start
-No.

00:58:39.212 --> 00:58:40.613 position:16% line:83% align:start
I appreciate everyone's
help, but it's

00:58:40.646 --> 00:58:42.215 position:16% line:89% align:start
time I left this place.

00:58:42.248 --> 00:58:43.116 position:24% line:89% align:start
KUSANAGI: Togusa!

00:59:04.337 --> 00:59:05.571 position:44% line:89% align:start
No!

00:59:05.605 --> 00:59:06.939 position:38% line:89% align:start
Togusa!

00:59:06.973 --> 00:59:08.975 position:10% line:83% align:start
What the hell happened here?
Come on.

00:59:09.008 --> 00:59:09.976 position:33% line:89% align:start
Talk to me.

00:59:10.009 --> 00:59:11.978 position:16% line:89% align:start
Dammit, Togusa, wake up!

00:59:12.011 --> 00:59:15.047 position:38% line:89% align:start
Togusa!

00:59:15.081 --> 00:59:16.449 position:27% line:83% align:start
So was there any
evidence to prove

00:59:16.483 --> 00:59:19.520 position:16% line:83% align:start
that this Aoi kid Togusa
mentioned ever existed?

00:59:19.553 --> 00:59:21.488 position:5% line:89% align:start
-I couldn't find a single trace.

00:59:21.522 --> 00:59:23.424 position:30% line:83% align:start
It's possible
someone deliberately

00:59:23.457 --> 00:59:26.993 position:7% line:83% align:start
altered the center's computer
files and the staff's memories.

00:59:27.026 --> 00:59:30.062 position:5% line:83% align:start
But I can't go too much further
using only Togusa's testimony.

00:59:30.096 --> 00:59:31.197 position:41% line:89% align:start
-Huh.

00:59:31.231 --> 00:59:34.201 position:13% line:83% align:start
That's why his report was
going to be a sketch, huh?

00:59:34.234 --> 00:59:36.370 position:24% line:83% align:start
-A handsome young
lad in a wheelchair

00:59:36.403 --> 00:59:38.505 position:10% line:89% align:start
with a lefty catcher's mitt.

00:59:38.539 --> 00:59:41.141 position:10% line:83% align:start
Togusa said he would use the
memories in his own cyberbrain

00:59:41.175 --> 00:59:43.009 position:33% line:83% align:start
to draw him.
-Wait.

00:59:43.043 --> 00:59:44.745 position:21% line:83% align:start
Did you say a lefty
catcher's mitt?

00:59:44.778 --> 00:59:46.547 position:16% line:89% align:start
That term is net jargon.

00:59:46.580 --> 00:59:49.683 position:7% line:83% align:start
It means something you think
is real when it actually isn't.

00:59:49.716 --> 00:59:51.752 position:10% line:89% align:start
TOGUSA: You sure about that?

00:59:51.785 --> 00:59:53.420 position:10% line:89% align:start
Sorry I took so long, Major.

00:59:53.454 --> 00:59:54.621 position:41% line:89% align:start
-Give.

00:59:54.655 --> 00:59:55.522 position:27% line:83% align:start
I want to see if
what you've got there

00:59:55.556 --> 00:59:58.158 position:24% line:83% align:start
is good enough to
save your sorry ass.

00:59:58.192 --> 01:00:00.027 position:16% line:89% align:start
-Now, don't be shocked.

01:00:00.060 --> 01:00:00.728 position:13% line:89% align:start
This shows I have talent.

01:00:07.201 --> 01:00:10.170 position:16% line:89% align:start
-What the hell is this?

01:00:10.204 --> 01:00:13.006 position:10% line:83% align:start
-Looks like you picked up a
bad case of weird memories

01:00:13.040 --> 01:00:14.141 position:24% line:89% align:start
in a weird place.

01:00:30.492 --> 01:00:32.494 position:21% line:83% align:start
TOGUSA: Just because
people didn't know me

01:00:32.527 --> 01:00:34.262 position:30% line:83% align:start
and because I
didn't know anybody,

01:00:34.295 --> 01:00:37.097 position:24% line:83% align:start
I thought what I'd
do is I'd pretend

01:00:37.131 --> 01:00:39.501 position:7% line:89% align:start
I was one of those deaf-mutes.

01:00:39.534 --> 01:00:41.569 position:24% line:83% align:start
I thought what I'd
do is I'd pretend

01:00:41.603 --> 01:00:45.206 position:7% line:89% align:start
I was one of those deaf-mutes.

01:00:45.240 --> 01:00:50.745 position:21% line:83% align:start
What I'd do was I'd
pretend I-- or should I?

01:00:58.553 --> 01:00:59.254 position:30% line:89% align:start
Wait a minute.

01:01:06.227 --> 01:01:08.731 position:13% line:83% align:start
KUSANAGI: So I hear you're
pursing the Salinger angle.

01:01:08.764 --> 01:01:11.332 position:41% line:89% align:start
-Yes.

01:01:11.366 --> 01:01:12.300 position:21% line:83% align:start
KUSANAGI: It's well
known that he wrote

01:01:12.333 --> 01:01:15.169 position:19% line:83% align:start
a short story entitled
"The Laughing Man."

01:01:15.203 --> 01:01:17.205 position:16% line:83% align:start
And there's no shortage
of people who point out

01:01:17.238 --> 01:01:21.175 position:16% line:83% align:start
the similarities between
his story and the crimes.

01:01:21.209 --> 01:01:24.313 position:5% line:83% align:start
Thing is, Special Investigations
HQ has already analyzed

01:01:24.346 --> 01:01:27.416 position:30% line:83% align:start
every possible
interpretation of that story.

01:01:27.449 --> 01:01:29.218 position:13% line:83% align:start
I don't think there's any
new take on the subject

01:01:29.251 --> 01:01:31.720 position:5% line:89% align:start
that's going to break the case.

01:01:31.754 --> 01:01:34.356 position:24% line:83% align:start
-But you've heard
art imitates life.

01:01:34.390 --> 01:01:37.159 position:21% line:83% align:start
The opposite should
be true, too.

01:01:37.192 --> 01:01:40.529 position:13% line:83% align:start
You know, I can't help but
think that the boy I met,

01:01:40.563 --> 01:01:44.166 position:10% line:83% align:start
the one at the aids center,
was actually the Laughing Man.

01:01:44.199 --> 01:01:46.335 position:19% line:83% align:start
-Hey, there have been
countless suspects.

01:01:46.368 --> 01:01:48.571 position:16% line:83% align:start
They all seemed certain
to be the Laughing Man.

01:01:48.604 --> 01:01:50.372 position:21% line:83% align:start
So in light of that,
what basis do you

01:01:50.406 --> 01:01:53.142 position:13% line:83% align:start
have for thinking this kid
is the genuine article?

01:01:53.175 --> 01:01:54.844 position:19% line:83% align:start
TOGUSA: Major, are you
familiar with the phrase

01:01:54.878 --> 01:01:57.881 position:16% line:83% align:start
around the Laughing Man
logo, and the meaning of it?

01:01:57.914 --> 01:01:59.682 position:41% line:89% align:start
-Yeah.

01:01:59.716 --> 01:02:02.518 position:7% line:83% align:start
I thought what I'd do was I'd
become one of those deaf-mutes.

01:02:02.551 --> 01:02:04.320 position:30% line:89% align:start
I understand.

01:02:04.353 --> 01:02:07.389 position:7% line:83% align:start
It's a quote from chapter 25%
of "The Catcher in the Rye."

01:02:07.423 --> 01:02:08.592 position:38% line:89% align:start
-Uh-huh.

01:02:08.625 --> 01:02:10.259 position:21% line:83% align:start
And like I included
in my report,

01:02:10.292 --> 01:02:13.530 position:10% line:83% align:start
I saw some of it written on
that panel at the center.

01:02:13.563 --> 01:02:16.900 position:7% line:83% align:start
At first, I convinced myself
it was verbatim from the novel.

01:02:16.933 --> 01:02:19.603 position:7% line:89% align:start
However, I realized something.

01:02:19.636 --> 01:02:22.606 position:10% line:83% align:start
The original quote ends with
"one of those deaf-mutes."

01:02:22.639 --> 01:02:25.675 position:7% line:89% align:start
But what I saw was different.

01:02:25.709 --> 01:02:27.277 position:30% line:89% align:start
"Or should I?"

01:02:27.310 --> 01:02:31.348 position:5% line:89% align:start
This little bit had been added.

01:02:31.381 --> 01:02:32.882 position:24% line:83% align:start
You don't suppose
it's a conversation he

01:02:32.916 --> 01:02:35.885 position:5% line:89% align:start
was having with himself, do you?

01:02:35.919 --> 01:02:37.921 position:21% line:83% align:start
Asking himself if he
should break his silence

01:02:37.954 --> 01:02:40.523 position:5% line:89% align:start
and go back out into the world?

01:02:40.557 --> 01:02:41.491 position:13% line:89% align:start
Tell me something, Major.

01:02:41.524 --> 01:02:43.660 position:5% line:89% align:start
Have you ever experienced this?

01:02:43.693 --> 01:02:46.329 position:16% line:83% align:start
When you try to imitate
an artist you admire,

01:02:46.363 --> 01:02:49.232 position:10% line:83% align:start
you want to get as close as
you can to the original work.

01:02:49.265 --> 01:02:52.669 position:24% line:83% align:start
So you try to make
a perfect copy.

01:02:52.702 --> 01:02:54.872 position:24% line:83% align:start
But here, we have
a boy who dared

01:02:54.905 --> 01:02:56.774 position:10% line:89% align:start
to modify Salinger's quote.

01:02:56.807 --> 01:02:58.441 position:30% line:83% align:start
He was able to
rewrite the end of it

01:02:58.475 --> 01:03:01.679 position:24% line:83% align:start
because this young
man was the original.

01:03:01.712 --> 01:03:03.380 position:27% line:83% align:start
-That theory is
awfully dependent

01:03:03.413 --> 01:03:05.382 position:16% line:89% align:start
on your personal views.

01:03:05.415 --> 01:03:08.284 position:5% line:83% align:start
You do realize it's far too weak
for you to base anything on,

01:03:08.318 --> 01:03:09.352 position:35% line:89% align:start
don't you?

01:03:09.386 --> 01:03:11.489 position:13% line:83% align:start
-Regardless of his cutting
edge hacking techniques,

01:03:11.522 --> 01:03:15.526 position:7% line:83% align:start
the Laughing Man kidnapped CEO
Serano, at gunpoint no less.

01:03:15.559 --> 01:03:17.795 position:7% line:83% align:start
These actions don't fit at all
with his technical abilities.

01:03:17.828 --> 01:03:20.398 position:10% line:83% align:start
Couldn't this mean that the
Laughing Man, despite the fact

01:03:20.431 --> 01:03:22.232 position:21% line:83% align:start
that he's so good at
hacking-- or should

01:03:22.265 --> 01:03:25.336 position:13% line:83% align:start
I say because he's good--
didn't place any value at all

01:03:25.369 --> 01:03:27.905 position:7% line:83% align:start
on electronic media, something
that could be rewritten?

01:03:27.938 --> 01:03:30.841 position:13% line:83% align:start
If you think about it, he
was after information that's

01:03:30.875 --> 01:03:33.411 position:21% line:83% align:start
stored in some sort
of physical medium.

01:03:33.444 --> 01:03:36.814 position:5% line:89% align:start
In other words, paper documents.

01:03:36.847 --> 01:03:39.350 position:10% line:83% align:start
-Do you want to investigate
this angle further?

01:03:39.383 --> 01:03:41.218 position:41% line:89% align:start
-Yes.

01:03:41.252 --> 01:03:43.354 position:16% line:83% align:start
-I was going to stop you
if you were doing this out

01:03:43.387 --> 01:03:47.224 position:21% line:83% align:start
of emotional revenge
for that center fiasco.

01:03:47.258 --> 01:03:48.960 position:21% line:83% align:start
But it could be your
ghost has finally

01:03:48.994 --> 01:03:50.728 position:7% line:89% align:start
begun whispering to you, too.

01:03:50.761 --> 01:03:51.562 position:35% line:83% align:start
All right.
Fine.

01:03:55.967 --> 01:03:57.301 position:30% line:89% align:start
You go ahead.

01:03:57.334 --> 01:03:57.936 position:24% line:89% align:start
Do what you want.

01:03:57.969 --> 01:03:58.904 position:16% line:89% align:start
I'll fill in the chief.

01:03:58.937 --> 01:04:00.404 position:19% line:89% align:start
-I appreciate, Major.

01:04:18.924 --> 01:04:20.358 position:24% line:89% align:start
-How's it coming?

01:04:23.595 --> 01:04:25.664 position:21% line:89% align:start
-This is a big job.

01:04:25.697 --> 01:04:26.998 position:21% line:89% align:start
Thanks for the help.

01:04:27.032 --> 01:04:29.935 position:27% line:89% align:start
And the coffee.

01:04:29.968 --> 01:04:30.802 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh.

01:04:30.836 --> 01:04:33.672 position:35% line:89% align:start
Found it.

01:04:33.705 --> 01:04:35.340 position:24% line:89% align:start
WOMAN: Found what?

01:04:35.373 --> 01:04:37.342 position:27% line:83% align:start
-More precisely,
something isn't here

01:04:37.375 --> 01:04:41.013 position:10% line:83% align:start
which ought to be-- the list
of Murai vaccine recipients.

01:04:41.047 --> 01:04:43.749 position:27% line:83% align:start
That file is the
only one missing.

01:04:43.782 --> 01:04:46.551 position:24% line:83% align:start
-I wonder how long
it's been gone.

01:04:46.585 --> 01:04:48.855 position:10% line:83% align:start
It's funny, I don't see how
stealing something like that

01:04:48.888 --> 01:04:50.789 position:13% line:89% align:start
would do anybody any good.

01:04:50.823 --> 01:04:53.558 position:16% line:83% align:start
-Is there anyone you can
think of who would want it?

01:04:53.592 --> 01:04:56.661 position:19% line:83% align:start
You know, someone the
file might be of value to?

01:04:56.695 --> 01:05:00.365 position:27% line:83% align:start
-Uh, well, if I
had to say, I would

01:05:00.398 --> 01:05:02.735 position:10% line:83% align:start
guess the Sunflower Society.
-Sunflower?

01:05:11.511 --> 01:05:14.413 position:24% line:83% align:start
TOGUSA: 2019 AD--
during that year,

01:05:14.447 --> 01:05:17.350 position:13% line:83% align:start
just as cyberization was
starting to become commonplace,

01:05:17.383 --> 01:05:19.952 position:13% line:83% align:start
cases of cyberbrain damage
of an unknown origin

01:05:19.986 --> 01:05:22.855 position:16% line:83% align:start
became a growing concern
in the medical community.

01:05:22.889 --> 01:05:25.591 position:19% line:83% align:start
It was discovered that
gradual hardening in the brain

01:05:25.625 --> 01:05:27.994 position:16% line:83% align:start
occurred in areas where
cyberization had been

01:05:28.027 --> 01:05:30.663 position:21% line:83% align:start
performed, resulting
in brain death.

01:05:30.696 --> 01:05:34.734 position:5% line:83% align:start
This condition later came to be
known as cyberbrain sclerosis.

01:05:34.767 --> 01:05:36.636 position:16% line:83% align:start
Although the likelihood
of displaying the symptoms

01:05:36.669 --> 01:05:38.805 position:21% line:83% align:start
is considerably low,
anyone who's been cyberized

01:05:38.838 --> 01:05:39.973 position:27% line:89% align:start
is susceptible.

01:05:40.007 --> 01:05:42.608 position:13% line:83% align:start
Because there was no basic
treatment once the symptoms

01:05:42.642 --> 01:05:44.744 position:16% line:83% align:start
appeared, it was called
the incurable disease

01:05:44.777 --> 01:05:47.114 position:21% line:83% align:start
of the 21st century,
following in the footsteps

01:05:47.147 --> 01:05:50.750 position:27% line:83% align:start
of tuberculosis,
cancer, and AIDS.

01:05:50.784 --> 01:05:53.854 position:19% line:83% align:start
The Murai vaccine is a
tumor suppressor, developed

01:05:53.887 --> 01:05:56.556 position:27% line:83% align:start
by an M.D. named
Jotose Murai, who

01:05:56.589 --> 01:05:59.458 position:19% line:83% align:start
created this specific
treat for the disease.

01:05:59.492 --> 01:06:01.829 position:21% line:83% align:start
However, the Medical
Association back then

01:06:01.862 --> 01:06:05.398 position:10% line:83% align:start
was dominated by proponents
of micro machine therapy.

01:06:05.431 --> 01:06:07.433 position:27% line:83% align:start
And many of them
voiced the opinion

01:06:07.466 --> 01:06:10.737 position:13% line:83% align:start
that the doctor's vaccine
was a step backwards.

01:06:10.771 --> 01:06:13.073 position:10% line:83% align:start
They were concerned that if
his research was approved,

01:06:13.106 --> 01:06:15.075 position:24% line:83% align:start
it might even hold
back the development

01:06:15.108 --> 01:06:17.144 position:7% line:89% align:start
of a micro machine treatment.

01:06:17.177 --> 01:06:19.146 position:24% line:83% align:start
Perhaps that's the
reason approval

01:06:19.179 --> 01:06:21.481 position:30% line:83% align:start
for the Murai
vaccine was shelved.

01:06:21.515 --> 01:06:24.618 position:24% line:83% align:start
And in February of
2021, Doctor Murai,

01:06:24.651 --> 01:06:26.820 position:19% line:83% align:start
who carried his dream
of a vaccine therapy

01:06:26.854 --> 01:06:31.391 position:16% line:83% align:start
to the very end, died a
broken man at the age of 68

01:06:31.425 --> 01:06:34.528 position:7% line:83% align:start
without seeing a decision from
the Drug Evaluation Council.

01:06:34.561 --> 01:06:37.131 position:24% line:83% align:start
Then, in April of
that same year,

01:06:37.165 --> 01:06:39.968 position:19% line:83% align:start
the vaccine, which had
been denied acceptance,

01:06:40.001 --> 01:06:43.905 position:10% line:83% align:start
was hastily sanctioned as a
fee-based clinical trial drug

01:06:43.938 --> 01:06:47.008 position:21% line:83% align:start
for use by specially
designated patients.

01:06:47.041 --> 01:06:50.011 position:10% line:83% align:start
The approval was never made
known to the general public.

01:06:50.044 --> 01:06:52.981 position:27% line:83% align:start
And the official
position on it today

01:06:53.014 --> 01:06:57.685 position:7% line:83% align:start
is that there are no patients
being treated with the vaccine.

01:06:57.719 --> 01:07:00.420 position:21% line:83% align:start
Even now, one group
remains actively

01:07:00.454 --> 01:07:04.025 position:13% line:83% align:start
interested in this fact--
the Sunflower Society,

01:07:04.058 --> 01:07:07.562 position:7% line:83% align:start
a nonprofit organization that
offers support to individuals

01:07:07.595 --> 01:07:09.797 position:19% line:83% align:start
who want to take major
companies and government

01:07:09.831 --> 01:07:12.734 position:10% line:83% align:start
agencies to court by filing
lawsuits against them.

01:07:21.643 --> 01:07:23.978 position:30% line:89% align:start
-Interesting.

01:07:24.012 --> 01:07:27.682 position:5% line:83% align:start
Looks like you've certainly done
your homework, I'll say that.

01:07:27.715 --> 01:07:31.019 position:19% line:83% align:start
So you're a freelance
journalist, are you?

01:07:31.052 --> 01:07:32.787 position:19% line:89% align:start
-My situation is this.

01:07:32.820 --> 01:07:35.790 position:21% line:83% align:start
I lost my father to
CS a few months back.

01:07:35.823 --> 01:07:37.659 position:16% line:83% align:start
he had been given micro
machine treatment up

01:07:37.692 --> 01:07:39.128 position:21% line:89% align:start
until the very end.

01:07:39.161 --> 01:07:41.629 position:13% line:83% align:start
But after he passed away,
I heard about your group

01:07:41.663 --> 01:07:43.866 position:10% line:89% align:start
and about the Murai vaccine.

01:07:43.899 --> 01:07:45.234 position:33% line:89% align:start
-Oh, I see.

01:07:45.267 --> 01:07:47.169 position:21% line:89% align:start
Sorry for your loss.

01:07:47.202 --> 01:07:48.871 position:27% line:83% align:start
-If only someone
had told us sooner

01:07:48.904 --> 01:07:51.774 position:13% line:83% align:start
about the vaccine and the
excellent results it's had,

01:07:51.807 --> 01:07:54.076 position:5% line:89% align:start
my father might be alive today.

01:07:54.109 --> 01:07:57.980 position:5% line:89% align:start
The thought of it is killing me.

01:07:58.013 --> 01:08:00.481 position:10% line:83% align:start
You see, before now, I never
took an interest in this.

01:08:00.515 --> 01:08:02.084 position:19% line:89% align:start
It didn't concern me.

01:08:02.117 --> 01:08:05.888 position:7% line:83% align:start
But if it can save people who
suffer from that awful disease,

01:08:05.921 --> 01:08:07.256 position:7% line:89% align:start
I'd like to offer my services.

01:08:07.289 --> 01:08:09.024 position:35% line:89% align:start
-How kind.

01:08:09.058 --> 01:08:11.660 position:16% line:83% align:start
A lot of people like you
filled with determination

01:08:11.694 --> 01:08:12.928 position:24% line:89% align:start
used to come here.

01:08:12.962 --> 01:08:15.998 position:16% line:83% align:start
But every single one of
them ended up failing.

01:08:16.031 --> 01:08:16.932 position:30% line:89% align:start
-They failed?

01:08:16.966 --> 01:08:18.534 position:33% line:89% align:start
Why is that?

01:08:18.567 --> 01:08:20.502 position:19% line:83% align:start
-There are individuals
who don't want the public

01:08:20.536 --> 01:08:23.706 position:13% line:83% align:start
to turn its back on micro
machines-- individuals

01:08:23.739 --> 01:08:25.107 position:27% line:89% align:start
from everywhere.

01:08:25.140 --> 01:08:27.576 position:19% line:89% align:start
-Just as I suspected.

01:08:27.609 --> 01:08:30.146 position:24% line:83% align:start
As luck would have
it, I have some pull

01:08:30.180 --> 01:08:31.680 position:7% line:89% align:start
in the entertainment industry.

01:08:31.714 --> 01:08:34.050 position:16% line:83% align:start
And from what I've heard
from my inside sources,

01:08:34.084 --> 01:08:35.784 position:30% line:83% align:start
there are even
people in the biz who

01:08:35.818 --> 01:08:38.989 position:24% line:83% align:start
have been secretly
receiving the vaccine.

01:08:39.022 --> 01:08:43.592 position:16% line:83% align:start
It's not easy to spread
unpleasant news like this.

01:08:43.625 --> 01:08:46.628 position:19% line:83% align:start
So if you want to get
people talking about it,

01:08:46.662 --> 01:08:49.065 position:10% line:83% align:start
I guess you'd need some sort
of scandal, wouldn't you?

01:08:49.099 --> 01:08:51.667 position:21% line:83% align:start
-Well, it's obvious
you did not come here

01:08:51.700 --> 01:08:53.770 position:19% line:83% align:start
to see us out of some
temporary emotion.

01:09:00.710 --> 01:09:03.913 position:27% line:83% align:start
In fact, we just
acquired a certain file.

01:09:03.947 --> 01:09:11.755 position:38% line:89% align:start
-A file?

01:09:11.788 --> 01:09:12.689 position:33% line:89% align:start
MAN: Dammit.

01:09:12.722 --> 01:09:14.824 position:30% line:89% align:start
I'm finished.

01:09:14.858 --> 01:09:17.127 position:21% line:83% align:start
I shouldn't have run
like that, since you

01:09:17.160 --> 01:09:18.828 position:5% line:89% align:start
