01:55:38.689 --> 01:55:41.024 position:21% line:83% align:start
Who else besides you
knows of this money trail?

01:55:41.059 --> 01:55:42.260 position:27% line:83% align:start
-Now that you've
read it, there's

01:55:42.293 --> 01:55:46.064 position:5% line:83% align:start
you, of course; Mr. Serano, who
decided to accuse Yakushima;

01:55:46.097 --> 01:55:46.998 position:16% line:89% align:start
and there are my people.

01:55:47.031 --> 01:55:48.765 position:33% line:89% align:start
That's all.

01:55:48.799 --> 01:55:49.766 position:38% line:89% align:start
-I see.

01:55:49.800 --> 01:55:51.102 position:27% line:89% align:start
Very well, then.

01:55:51.135 --> 01:55:53.104 position:19% line:83% align:start
As for Mr. Yakushima,
we'll deal with him

01:55:53.137 --> 01:55:55.106 position:13% line:89% align:start
when the timing is right.

01:55:55.139 --> 01:55:57.108 position:24% line:83% align:start
However, with the
lower house elections,

01:55:57.141 --> 01:55:59.509 position:10% line:89% align:start
we're in a crucial time now.

01:55:59.543 --> 01:56:01.045 position:24% line:83% align:start
I want the public
and the media to feel

01:56:01.079 --> 01:56:03.480 position:10% line:89% align:start
as if they've won a victory.

01:56:03.513 --> 01:56:06.117 position:24% line:83% align:start
If I let a man as
powerful as Yakushima go,

01:56:06.150 --> 01:56:09.787 position:7% line:83% align:start
proportional casualties on our
side are very likely to occur.

01:56:09.821 --> 01:56:11.890 position:16% line:83% align:start
-I don't understand what
you're trying to imply,

01:56:11.923 --> 01:56:12.657 position:27% line:89% align:start
Prime Minister.

01:56:15.960 --> 01:56:17.929 position:19% line:83% align:start
-I mean passage of the
Special Forces Bill.

01:56:28.139 --> 01:56:29.941 position:33% line:83% align:start
-Hey, Chief.
-Mmhm.

01:56:29.974 --> 01:56:37.216 position:7% line:89% align:start
TOGUSA: They're following us.

01:57:07.146 --> 01:57:09.081 position:24% line:83% align:start
MAN: The enemy has
nine think tank units.

01:57:09.114 --> 01:57:11.583 position:13% line:83% align:start
Squads three and four, you
will drop in from above

01:57:11.617 --> 01:57:13.552 position:24% line:83% align:start
and infiltrate the
hangar from the heliport.

01:57:13.585 --> 01:57:16.255 position:16% line:83% align:start
Your top priority is the
destruction of the tanks.

01:57:16.288 --> 01:57:18.190 position:27% line:83% align:start
Squads five and
six, quickly capture

01:57:18.223 --> 01:57:20.059 position:21% line:83% align:start
the seventh primary
members and gain

01:57:20.092 --> 01:57:21.694 position:5% line:89% align:start
control of the entire facility.

01:57:21.727 --> 01:57:23.929 position:19% line:83% align:start
All units, go autistic
once we're in.

01:57:23.963 --> 01:57:26.632 position:16% line:83% align:start
These people specialize
in information warfare.

01:57:26.665 --> 01:57:28.701 position:21% line:83% align:start
We'll pin them down
with brute force.

01:58:00.000 --> 01:58:02.268 position:30% line:89% align:start
-Wait, Chief.

01:58:02.302 --> 01:58:04.004 position:27% line:83% align:start
-We came here to
pick you up, sir.

01:58:04.037 --> 01:58:06.139 position:10% line:83% align:start
There are still a few things
you need to do for us.

01:58:10.643 --> 01:58:12.545 position:27% line:83% align:start
-Making all the
necessary arrangements

01:58:12.579 --> 01:58:14.247 position:5% line:89% align:start
in such a short amount of time.

01:58:14.280 --> 01:58:17.083 position:19% line:83% align:start
The prime minister is
certainly a capable man.

01:58:17.117 --> 01:58:19.686 position:7% line:83% align:start
OFFICER: Section 9 is probably
being neutralized as we speak.

01:58:19.719 --> 01:58:26.260 position:30% line:89% align:start
-Neutralized?

01:58:26.293 --> 01:58:27.560 position:27% line:89% align:start
-Take him away.

01:58:27.594 --> 01:58:29.263 position:24% line:89% align:start
OFFICER: Yes, sir.

01:58:29.296 --> 01:58:30.231 position:30% line:89% align:start
-Wait, Chief.

01:58:30.264 --> 01:58:31.164 position:27% line:89% align:start
What's going on?

01:58:31.198 --> 01:58:32.799 position:30% line:89% align:start
What is this?

01:58:32.832 --> 01:58:34.000 position:13% line:89% align:start
Please, explain it to me.

01:58:34.034 --> 01:58:34.968 position:41% line:89% align:start
Chief!

01:58:35.001 --> 01:58:35.902 position:38% line:89% align:start
Tell me!

01:58:45.312 --> 01:58:46.679 position:24% line:83% align:start
BATOU: Is it just
me, or does something

01:58:46.713 --> 01:58:47.847 position:30% line:83% align:start
seem different
about the building?

01:58:47.882 --> 01:58:49.917 position:27% line:83% align:start
And what's with
this mustard call?

01:58:49.950 --> 01:58:51.785 position:19% line:89% align:start
It was a little weird.

01:58:51.819 --> 01:58:53.720 position:7% line:83% align:start
KUSANAGI: I don't have time to
fill you in on the situation

01:58:53.753 --> 01:58:54.654 position:35% line:89% align:start
right now.

01:58:54.687 --> 01:58:56.656 position:21% line:83% align:start
Just keep quiet and
carry out my orders.

01:58:56.689 --> 01:58:58.658 position:27% line:83% align:start
Prep six generic
prosthetic bodies,

01:58:58.691 --> 01:59:00.928 position:24% line:83% align:start
and bring them to
the command center.

01:59:00.961 --> 01:59:02.096 position:35% line:89% align:start
BATOU: Hm?

01:59:02.129 --> 01:59:03.130 position:38% line:89% align:start
Hold on.

01:59:03.164 --> 01:59:04.965 position:27% line:89% align:start
Are you saying--

01:59:04.999 --> 01:59:05.833 position:21% line:89% align:start
KUSANAGI: Get to it.

01:59:17.278 --> 01:59:18.746 position:38% line:89% align:start
-Major.

01:59:18.779 --> 01:59:20.281 position:16% line:83% align:start
You want to tell us what
the hell's going on?

01:59:24.952 --> 01:59:27.255 position:13% line:89% align:start
-You two take these seeds.

01:59:27.289 --> 01:59:29.391 position:16% line:83% align:start
Once we get out of here,
leak the information

01:59:29.424 --> 01:59:31.625 position:19% line:83% align:start
and then let it sprout
among the media.

01:59:31.659 --> 01:59:33.395 position:13% line:83% align:start
We'll need a push to oust
the secretary general.

02:00:14.069 --> 02:00:16.204 position:19% line:83% align:start
-Verify the situation,
and see to the wounded

02:00:16.238 --> 02:00:17.839 position:19% line:89% align:start
on the double, dammit.

02:00:22.777 --> 02:00:24.179 position:30% line:83% align:start
TACHIKOMA: Oh,
goodness gracious.

02:00:24.212 --> 02:00:26.449 position:24% line:83% align:start
What are we going
to do with you?

02:00:26.482 --> 02:00:29.050 position:19% line:83% align:start
You know you shouldn't
spill your tea like that.

02:00:29.084 --> 02:00:30.051 position:35% line:89% align:start
[humming]

02:00:30.085 --> 02:00:31.220 position:35% line:89% align:start
Hey, look.

02:00:31.254 --> 02:00:32.221 position:27% line:89% align:start
The news is on.

02:00:32.255 --> 02:00:33.456 position:27% line:89% align:start
Let's watch TV.

02:00:33.489 --> 02:00:34.390 position:10% line:83% align:start
REPORTER: We interrupt this
program to bring you breaking

02:00:34.423 --> 02:00:36.758 position:24% line:83% align:start
news on the latest
Section 9 developments.

02:00:36.791 --> 02:00:39.028 position:10% line:83% align:start
An emergency cabinet meeting
passed a special forces

02:00:39.061 --> 02:00:41.297 position:19% line:83% align:start
restriction bill aimed
at military deployments

02:00:41.330 --> 02:00:44.866 position:10% line:5% align:start
after urging the dismantling
of Public Security Section 9.

02:00:44.901 --> 02:00:47.403 position:7% line:5% align:start
Special forces stormed Section
9's facility moments ago

02:00:47.436 --> 02:00:49.704 position:10% line:5% align:start
when they failed to respond
to repeated warnings,

02:00:49.738 --> 02:00:52.475 position:7% line:5% align:start
indicating the group's intent
to maintain this standoff.

02:00:52.508 --> 02:00:54.911 position:27% line:83% align:start
We now take you
live to the scene.

02:00:54.944 --> 02:00:56.979 position:16% line:83% align:start
REPORTER: A short while
ago above the building

02:00:57.013 --> 02:01:00.750 position:27% line:83% align:start
which houses the
Section 9 complex--

02:01:00.783 --> 02:01:02.718 position:13% line:83% align:start
KUSANAGI: From here, we'll
go off in three directions

02:01:02.752 --> 02:01:04.320 position:24% line:83% align:start
in order to split
up our pursuers.

02:01:04.353 --> 02:01:06.355 position:21% line:83% align:start
After that, we go to
ground in the city

02:01:06.389 --> 02:01:08.291 position:10% line:89% align:start
and head our separate ways.

02:01:08.324 --> 02:01:10.726 position:24% line:83% align:start
Security Section 9
has now disbanded.

02:01:10.760 --> 02:01:11.827 position:33% line:89% align:start
That is all.

02:01:18.100 --> 02:01:20.002 position:27% line:83% align:start
-They're several
damaged, but we believe

02:01:20.036 --> 02:01:21.270 position:19% line:83% align:start
these are the corpses
of the six members.

02:01:21.305 --> 02:01:25.342 position:5% line:83% align:start
We're analyzing the cyberbrains
for traces of residual usage.

02:01:25.375 --> 02:01:27.810 position:5% line:83% align:start
-Call squad five in here while
you're waiting for the results.

02:01:27.843 --> 02:01:29.446 position:27% line:83% align:start
Assume that this
operation is camouflaged

02:01:29.479 --> 02:01:31.448 position:19% line:83% align:start
and seal off any exit
you can think of,

02:01:31.481 --> 02:01:33.749 position:19% line:83% align:start
including the elevator
shafts, ventilation

02:01:33.783 --> 02:01:35.385 position:7% line:83% align:start
ducts, and every sewer outlet.
-Yes, sir.

02:01:41.491 --> 02:01:44.061 position:19% line:83% align:start
BATOU: So, Section 9's
finally finished, huh?

02:01:44.094 --> 02:01:45.462 position:16% line:83% align:start
All the blood and sweat
we poured into just

02:01:45.495 --> 02:01:47.497 position:16% line:89% align:start
went poof, up in smoke.

02:01:47.531 --> 02:01:49.199 position:41% line:89% align:start
-Yeah.

02:01:49.233 --> 02:01:50.434 position:13% line:83% align:start
Free access to the latest
maintenance and cutting edge

02:01:50.467 --> 02:01:53.203 position:7% line:83% align:start
equipment was a sweet set up,
but when you get down to it,

02:01:53.237 --> 02:01:54.771 position:13% line:89% align:start
that's really all it was.

02:01:54.805 --> 02:01:57.474 position:13% line:83% align:start
The only thing we need to
do is find a new sponsor.

02:01:57.507 --> 02:01:59.142 position:10% line:89% align:start
Or is there something else?

02:01:59.176 --> 02:02:01.945 position:13% line:83% align:start
Have you got some kind of
attachment to the place, Batou?

02:02:01.979 --> 02:02:03.814 position:27% line:83% align:start
-Hm, not if you
put it like that.

02:02:03.847 --> 02:02:05.415 position:24% line:83% align:start
If anything, it's
the good and bad

02:02:05.449 --> 02:02:07.284 position:5% line:89% align:start
times we had-- all the memories.

02:02:07.317 --> 02:02:08.486 position:21% line:89% align:start
KUSANAGI: Memories?

02:02:08.519 --> 02:02:12.923 position:30% line:83% align:start
That's awfully
sentimental of you.

02:02:12.956 --> 02:02:14.958 position:21% line:83% align:start
-While we're on the
subject, that reminds me.

02:02:14.992 --> 02:02:17.294 position:24% line:83% align:start
Where's that watch
you're usually wearing.

02:02:17.327 --> 02:02:19.364 position:16% line:83% align:start
-I had to pick today to
leave it next to my bed

02:02:19.397 --> 02:02:20.797 position:24% line:89% align:start
at my safe house.

02:02:20.831 --> 02:02:21.898 position:24% line:83% align:start
Since they've hit
Section 9, they've

02:02:21.932 --> 02:02:24.402 position:27% line:83% align:start
probably got my
place secured, too.

02:02:24.435 --> 02:02:26.970 position:21% line:83% align:start
-That sucks, because
I seem to remember

02:02:27.004 --> 02:02:29.140 position:13% line:83% align:start
you got that as a gift to
mark the occasion of your very

02:02:29.173 --> 02:02:31.242 position:7% line:89% align:start
last prosthetic body resizing.

02:02:31.276 --> 02:02:34.345 position:27% line:83% align:start
But I don't know
who gave it to you.

02:02:34.379 --> 02:02:35.413 position:30% line:89% align:start
-So you knew?

02:02:35.446 --> 02:02:37.348 position:5% line:89% align:start
Well, don't get the wrong idea.

02:02:37.382 --> 02:02:39.384 position:13% line:83% align:start
I didn't actually wear it
for sentimental reasons.

02:02:46.357 --> 02:02:48.893 position:13% line:89% align:start
Well, enough idle chatter.

02:02:48.926 --> 02:02:50.528 position:5% line:83% align:start
Once we're out of here, we can't
get in touch with each other

02:02:50.561 --> 02:02:52.130 position:41% line:89% align:start
again.

02:02:52.163 --> 02:02:54.999 position:19% line:83% align:start
Even if we do meet, I
might not be who I am now.

02:02:55.033 --> 02:02:57.435 position:10% line:83% align:start
I want you to give your own
survival top priority, Batou.

02:03:10.582 --> 02:03:12.850 position:13% line:89% align:start
-We should split up here.

02:03:12.884 --> 02:03:13.485 position:33% line:89% align:start
-All right.

02:03:43.449 --> 02:03:45.384 position:24% line:83% align:start
-Hell, this is my
life, isn't it?

02:03:45.417 --> 02:03:47.152 position:16% line:83% align:start
How I decide to waste it
is my own damn business.

02:04:07.540 --> 02:04:12.545 position:10% line:83% align:start
TACHIKOMA: That report about
Section 9 has me worried.

02:04:12.579 --> 02:04:14.347 position:21% line:83% align:start
OLD MAN: The battle
is going badly.

02:04:14.381 --> 02:04:20.219 position:41% line:89% align:start
-Huh?

02:04:20.253 --> 02:04:21.153 position:38% line:89% align:start
I know.

02:04:21.186 --> 02:04:23.623 position:21% line:89% align:start
It sure is, mister.

02:04:23.656 --> 02:04:26.192 position:13% line:89% align:start
The battle is going badly.

02:04:26.226 --> 02:04:28.495 position:19% line:83% align:start
You know the building
that blew up last night?

02:04:28.528 --> 02:04:30.263 position:10% line:89% align:start
That's where I used to live.

02:04:30.296 --> 02:04:32.332 position:19% line:89% align:start
The place was my home.

02:04:32.365 --> 02:04:34.634 position:19% line:83% align:start
It's pretty nice here.
I can't complain.

02:04:34.667 --> 02:04:37.203 position:7% line:89% align:start
And I like all you old folks.

02:04:37.237 --> 02:04:38.271 position:35% line:89% align:start
You're OK.

02:04:38.304 --> 02:04:42.409 position:16% line:83% align:start
But there's someone that
I really want to go help.

02:04:42.442 --> 02:04:43.710 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

02:04:43.743 --> 02:04:48.081 position:10% line:89% align:start
-The battle is going badly.

02:04:48.114 --> 02:04:50.350 position:19% line:83% align:start
TACHIKOMA: Mister, is
that what I think it is?

02:04:50.383 --> 02:04:52.318 position:27% line:89% align:start
Mister, thanks!

02:04:52.352 --> 02:04:53.620 position:24% line:89% align:start
I'm gonna go now.

02:05:06.166 --> 02:05:09.402 position:35% line:89% align:start
Aw, Batou.

02:05:09.437 --> 02:05:11.371 position:19% line:89% align:start
TACHIKOMA: Hey there!

02:05:11.405 --> 02:05:14.040 position:21% line:83% align:start
TACHIKOMA: What are
you guys doing here?

02:05:14.073 --> 02:05:16.109 position:19% line:83% align:start
-Once a problem child,
always a problem child.

02:05:16.142 --> 02:05:17.344 position:19% line:89% align:start
Know what I'm saying.

02:05:17.378 --> 02:05:19.647 position:7% line:83% align:start
This means each of us had the
same thought even though we

02:05:19.680 --> 02:05:21.515 position:5% line:89% align:start
were independent of each other.

02:05:21.549 --> 02:05:22.683 position:27% line:83% align:start
One thing we all
share in common is

02:05:22.716 --> 02:05:25.753 position:7% line:83% align:start
the desire to help Mr. Batou.
-Right.

02:05:25.786 --> 02:05:26.953 position:24% line:83% align:start
And besides, it's
impossible for you

02:05:26.986 --> 02:05:28.756 position:10% line:83% align:start
to load that Howitzer shell
you're holding by yourself,

02:05:28.789 --> 02:05:29.723 position:35% line:89% align:start
isn't it?

02:05:29.757 --> 02:05:31.292 position:41% line:89% align:start
-Yeah.

02:05:31.325 --> 02:05:34.361 position:21% line:83% align:start
But are we the only
Tachikomas who came here?

02:05:34.395 --> 02:05:36.664 position:19% line:83% align:start
-Out of all of us that
were sent back to the lab,

02:05:36.697 --> 02:05:38.332 position:7% line:89% align:start
I'm the only one who survived.

02:05:38.365 --> 02:05:40.734 position:16% line:83% align:start
They just left me lying
around hooked up to equipment

02:05:40.768 --> 02:05:43.137 position:24% line:83% align:start
for final testing
like some specimen.

02:05:43.170 --> 02:05:46.006 position:21% line:83% align:start
So I ripped out the
cords and ran away!

02:05:46.040 --> 02:05:48.142 position:5% line:83% align:start
-I couldn't stop wondering what
was going on while I was doing

02:05:48.175 --> 02:05:50.177 position:19% line:83% align:start
high altitude work at
a construction site.

02:05:50.211 --> 02:05:52.112 position:30% line:89% align:start
How about you?

02:05:52.146 --> 02:05:54.248 position:27% line:83% align:start
-I'd say it was
pretty much the same.

02:05:54.281 --> 02:05:57.485 position:16% line:83% align:start
But what happened to the
rest who went to the lab?

02:05:57.518 --> 02:06:00.187 position:7% line:83% align:start
-They're all having structural
analyses run on them.

02:06:00.221 --> 02:06:01.690 position:24% line:83% align:start
They had their AIs
removed to help them run

02:06:01.723 --> 02:06:03.692 position:5% line:89% align:start
simulations on the Laughing Man.

02:06:03.725 --> 02:06:05.259 position:19% line:89% align:start
But do you know what?

02:06:05.292 --> 02:06:07.529 position:7% line:83% align:start
Everyone who had their brains
taken apart-- they kinda

02:06:07.562 --> 02:06:10.699 position:27% line:83% align:start
looked like they
were enjoying it.

02:06:10.732 --> 02:06:12.166 position:33% line:89% align:start
-Oh, I see.

02:06:35.323 --> 02:06:36.658 position:16% line:89% align:start
BATOU: That's my major.

02:06:36.691 --> 02:06:37.726 position:13% line:89% align:start
She doesn't miss a trick.

02:06:37.759 --> 02:06:38.627 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

02:07:24.707 --> 02:07:26.175 position:30% line:89% align:start
-Don't do it!

02:07:26.208 --> 02:07:29.478 position:24% line:89% align:start
Drop your weapon.

02:07:29.512 --> 02:07:31.280 position:35% line:89% align:start
-Yeah, OK.

02:07:31.314 --> 02:07:32.114 position:35% line:89% align:start
I give up.

02:08:20.931 --> 02:08:22.633 position:41% line:89% align:start
Score.

02:08:22.666 --> 02:08:24.468 position:10% line:83% align:start
I knew the major would have
a stash hidden around here.

02:08:44.688 --> 02:08:46.758 position:21% line:83% align:start
OFFICER: You finally
done putting up a fight?

02:09:00.838 --> 02:09:03.306 position:21% line:89% align:start
Damn, I killed him.

02:09:03.340 --> 02:09:04.442 position:30% line:83% align:start
-What's wrong?
Right.

02:09:04.475 --> 02:09:05.109 position:35% line:89% align:start
I forgot.

02:09:05.143 --> 02:09:06.611 position:10% line:89% align:start
I look dead to you, don't I?

02:09:06.644 --> 02:09:07.445 position:24% line:89% align:start
Don't believe it.

02:09:10.515 --> 02:09:12.917 position:21% line:83% align:start
I'm sorry, but I had
to hack your eyes, pal.

02:09:39.711 --> 02:09:41.579 position:27% line:89% align:start
You're kidding.

02:09:41.612 --> 02:09:42.346 position:30% line:89% align:start
There's more?

02:09:54.660 --> 02:09:59.932 position:35% line:89% align:start
[grunting]

02:09:59.965 --> 02:10:02.601 position:19% line:83% align:start
-You didn't have to go
and kill my partner.

02:10:02.634 --> 02:10:05.336 position:7% line:89% align:start
You're not coming back alive.

02:10:05.369 --> 02:10:11.643 position:5% line:89% align:start
A corpse will do good for that.

02:10:11.677 --> 02:10:14.580 position:13% line:83% align:start
I wanna give you this for
my buddies you killed.

02:10:23.889 --> 02:10:26.425 position:10% line:89% align:start
This is for my dead partner.

02:10:36.401 --> 02:10:38.670 position:35% line:89% align:start
What the--

02:10:38.704 --> 02:10:39.304 position:24% line:89% align:start
-Now's our chance.

02:10:39.338 --> 02:10:41.640 position:13% line:89% align:start
Get Mr. Batou out of here.

02:10:41.673 --> 02:10:44.610 position:38% line:89% align:start
-Right.

02:10:44.643 --> 02:10:45.410 position:30% line:89% align:start
-Think tanks?

02:10:54.888 --> 02:10:57.757 position:24% line:89% align:start
-I'll go in first.

02:10:57.791 --> 02:10:58.658 position:35% line:89% align:start
Mr. Batou.

02:10:58.691 --> 02:11:00.960 position:19% line:89% align:start
I'm sorry I was late.

02:11:00.994 --> 02:11:04.831 position:13% line:83% align:start
It took us a while to tap
into their com signals.

02:11:04.864 --> 02:11:05.765 position:33% line:89% align:start
Don't worry.

02:11:05.799 --> 02:11:06.733 position:21% line:89% align:start
We'll take that guy.

02:11:06.766 --> 02:11:08.935 position:21% line:89% align:start
You can count on it.

02:11:08.968 --> 02:11:11.437 position:19% line:83% align:start
Wait right here until
we get back, OK?

02:11:11.471 --> 02:11:19.946 position:24% line:83% align:start
-Son of a-- where
the hell were they?

02:11:19.979 --> 02:11:21.614 position:24% line:89% align:start
-I've got a plan.

02:11:21.648 --> 02:11:23.349 position:19% line:83% align:start
Think you can pin him
own with your wires?

02:11:23.383 --> 02:11:24.584 position:19% line:89% align:start
-I'll give it a shot.

02:11:24.617 --> 02:11:25.485 position:41% line:89% align:start
Uh-oh!

02:11:59.419 --> 02:12:00.688 position:16% line:89% align:start
TACHIKOMA: Easy does it.

02:12:00.721 --> 02:12:01.722 position:30% line:89% align:start
Don't rush it.

02:12:01.755 --> 02:12:03.591 position:19% line:89% align:start
I only have one shot.

02:12:14.735 --> 02:12:15.703 position:41% line:89% align:start
-Now!

02:12:15.736 --> 02:12:17.671 position:41% line:83% align:start
Shoot!
-Right!

02:12:22.977 --> 02:12:25.479 position:38% line:89% align:start
[shout]

02:12:30.018 --> 02:12:33.154 position:27% line:89% align:start
You're kidding!

02:12:33.188 --> 02:12:34.655 position:33% line:89% align:start
It's a dud.

02:12:37.558 --> 02:12:38.692 position:24% line:89% align:start
-I'm still alive?

02:12:51.740 --> 02:12:53.875 position:38% line:89% align:start
Oh, god.

02:12:53.909 --> 02:13:00.148 position:13% line:83% align:start
We're weak and powerless,
my fellow Tachikomas and I.

02:13:00.181 --> 02:13:02.751 position:13% line:89% align:start
KUSANAGI: That's not true.

02:13:02.784 --> 02:13:05.053 position:27% line:83% align:start
What you and the
others have gained

02:13:05.086 --> 02:13:06.454 position:7% line:89% align:start
makes you far from powerless.

02:13:11.927 --> 02:13:12.694 position:33% line:89% align:start
-That voice.

02:13:18.900 --> 02:13:20.169 position:13% line:89% align:start
This is the last I've got.

02:13:28.177 --> 02:13:30.612 position:44% line:83% align:start
Now!
-Right.

02:13:33.848 --> 02:13:37.119 position:35% line:89% align:start
Mr. Batou.

02:13:37.153 --> 02:13:38.586 position:21% line:89% align:start
Goodbye, Mr. Batou.

02:14:05.081 --> 02:14:07.883 position:10% line:89% align:start
-What were they doing here?

02:14:07.917 --> 02:14:09.685 position:16% line:83% align:start
KUSANAGI: The only thing
they could think about

02:14:09.719 --> 02:14:14.123 position:16% line:83% align:start
was saving you, so they
escaped from the lab.

02:14:14.156 --> 02:14:15.725 position:30% line:89% align:start
BATOU: Major.

02:14:15.758 --> 02:14:17.260 position:33% line:89% align:start
is that you?

02:14:17.294 --> 02:14:19.028 position:16% line:83% align:start
-I was the one who made
the call that they were

02:14:19.061 --> 02:14:20.663 position:24% line:83% align:start
useless as weapons
because they're

02:14:20.696 --> 02:14:23.033 position:10% line:89% align:start
AI had evolved too quickly.

02:14:23.066 --> 02:14:24.567 position:30% line:83% align:start
But the entire
time that they were

02:14:24.600 --> 02:14:26.769 position:24% line:83% align:start
busy pursuing the
accumulation of data

02:14:26.802 --> 02:14:29.638 position:19% line:83% align:start
and synchronizing with
each other again and again,

02:14:29.672 --> 02:14:32.742 position:30% line:83% align:start
they were also
acquiring individuality.

02:14:32.775 --> 02:14:34.044 position:30% line:89% align:start
I never knew.

02:14:34.077 --> 02:14:35.544 position:27% line:89% align:start
Not an inkling.

02:14:35.578 --> 02:14:39.116 position:16% line:83% align:start
They even became capable
of self sacrifice.

02:14:39.149 --> 02:14:41.952 position:13% line:83% align:start
If only I'd realized that
sooner instead of now when it's

02:14:41.985 --> 02:14:44.855 position:16% line:83% align:start
too late, because maybe
then I could have found out

02:14:44.888 --> 02:14:46.923 position:16% line:83% align:start
whether or not what the
Tachikoma had acquired

02:14:46.957 --> 02:14:49.126 position:33% line:89% align:start
were ghosts.

02:14:49.159 --> 02:14:51.661 position:30% line:89% align:start
BATOU: Ghosts?

02:14:51.695 --> 02:14:53.797 position:30% line:83% align:start
-Well, if they
hadn't shown up here,

02:14:53.830 --> 02:14:57.734 position:24% line:83% align:start
then you would be
dead right now.

02:14:57.768 --> 02:14:58.802 position:30% line:89% align:start
Let's move it.

02:14:58.835 --> 02:15:02.039 position:19% line:89% align:start
[helicopters humming]

02:15:14.017 --> 02:15:16.320 position:16% line:89% align:start
-Nice view of Section 9.

02:15:16.354 --> 02:15:17.988 position:16% line:83% align:start
You could pick anywhere
in the world to live,

02:15:18.021 --> 02:15:19.656 position:21% line:83% align:start
but here's where you
choose a safe house?

02:15:23.027 --> 02:15:25.129 position:44% line:83% align:start
Hey.
Hm?

02:15:34.704 --> 02:15:36.606 position:5% line:89% align:start
This body has always suited me.

02:15:36.640 --> 02:15:37.341 position:24% line:89% align:start
No other will do.

02:15:42.013 --> 02:15:46.717 position:16% line:83% align:start
-Huh, that was a remote
puppet the whole time?

02:15:46.751 --> 02:15:47.618 position:38% line:89% align:start
-Uh-huh.

02:16:00.731 --> 02:16:04.001 position:21% line:89% align:start
[helicopter humming]

02:16:13.878 --> 02:16:16.281 position:21% line:83% align:start
-By the way, I have
something of yours

02:16:16.315 --> 02:16:17.748 position:5% line:89% align:start
that almost didn't make it here.

02:16:20.852 --> 02:16:23.021 position:21% line:89% align:start
KUSANAGI: I knew it.

02:16:23.055 --> 02:16:25.057 position:13% line:83% align:start
BATOU: No matter how many
prosthetic bodies you went

02:16:25.090 --> 02:16:27.825 position:13% line:83% align:start
through, this was the one
thing that was always ticking

02:16:27.859 --> 02:16:31.096 position:24% line:83% align:start
away, keeping the
same time as you.

02:16:31.130 --> 02:16:33.031 position:19% line:83% align:start
In the midst of life's
fleeting moments,

02:16:33.065 --> 02:16:35.267 position:21% line:83% align:start
people entrust their
memories to external devices,

02:16:35.300 --> 02:16:38.036 position:7% line:83% align:start
because they want to set down
solid physical proof that

02:16:38.070 --> 02:16:41.773 position:21% line:83% align:start
can distinguish them
as unique individuals.

02:16:41.807 --> 02:16:44.843 position:19% line:83% align:start
That watch is all you
have, though, isn't it?

02:16:44.877 --> 02:16:47.713 position:5% line:83% align:start
Your only external memory device
that identifies the person

02:16:47.746 --> 02:16:48.947 position:5% line:89% align:start
you've been up till this minute.

02:16:51.950 --> 02:16:54.253 position:5% line:89% align:start
-Those are pretty serious words.

02:16:54.286 --> 02:16:58.023 position:16% line:83% align:start
I'd really like to know
where you got them from.

02:16:58.056 --> 02:17:01.293 position:24% line:83% align:start
A watch and weight
training gear.

02:17:01.326 --> 02:17:04.297 position:5% line:83% align:start
Both of us have clung to useless
scraps of memory, haven't we?

02:17:07.199 --> 02:17:10.836 position:7% line:83% align:start
In all probability, you and I
are the only members of Section

02:17:10.869 --> 02:17:14.006 position:24% line:83% align:start
9 who haven't been
arrested or killed yet.

02:17:14.039 --> 02:17:16.309 position:10% line:83% align:start
Let's make sure that we both
stay alive, at least long

02:17:16.342 --> 02:17:19.811 position:5% line:83% align:start
enough to leave behind a record
of what we tried to accomplish.

02:17:19.845 --> 02:17:20.913 position:41% line:89% align:start
-Yeah.

02:17:20.946 --> 02:17:22.881 position:10% line:83% align:start
I'm not about to die without
completing my mission.

02:17:46.406 --> 02:17:49.742 position:16% line:83% align:start
OFFICER: Primary sniping
target, Motoko Kusanagi.

02:17:49.776 --> 02:17:54.747 position:10% line:83% align:start
The committee has issued an
order for her termination.

02:17:54.781 --> 02:17:57.518 position:5% line:89% align:start
We've only got one shot at this.

02:17:57.551 --> 02:18:00.019 position:24% line:83% align:start
Take her out when
she's climbing aboard.

02:18:00.053 --> 02:18:00.920 position:38% line:89% align:start
-Motoko!

02:18:44.365 --> 02:18:47.101 position:33% line:83% align:start
Motoko, no!
Motoko!

02:18:47.134 --> 02:18:51.805 position:38% line:89% align:start
Dammit!

02:18:54.609 --> 02:18:56.578 position:21% line:89% align:start
-No vitals detected.

02:18:56.611 --> 02:18:59.280 position:7% line:89% align:start
Target destruction confirmed.

02:18:59.313 --> 02:19:09.089 position:10% line:89% align:start
-You dummy sons of-- Motoko!

02:19:09.123 --> 02:19:17.132 position:7% line:89% align:start
LAUGHING MAN: You mean to tell

02:19:17.165 --> 02:19:20.068 position:13% line:83% align:start
lost, a person's thoughts
can wander the net

02:19:20.101 --> 02:19:22.537 position:19% line:83% align:start
and continue to exist
as a unique individual?

02:19:22.570 --> 02:19:24.406 position:13% line:89% align:start
KUSANAGI: I'm not so sure.

02:19:24.439 --> 02:19:27.509 position:10% line:83% align:start
It's hard to imagine that a
will which is free of its shell

02:19:27.542 --> 02:19:31.313 position:5% line:83% align:start
could maintain its individuality
in the sea of the net.

02:19:31.346 --> 02:19:33.315 position:7% line:83% align:start
LAUGHING MAN: Then for someone
that continuously loses

02:19:33.348 --> 02:19:36.584 position:5% line:83% align:start
their individuality as they live
on, this is a world of despair.

02:19:36.618 --> 02:19:40.055 position:7% line:83% align:start
KUSANAGI: I guess that depends
on your definition of despair.

02:19:40.088 --> 02:19:41.990 position:10% line:83% align:start
Besides, there's always the
option of giving death a try,

02:19:42.023 --> 02:19:43.191 position:41% line:89% align:start
right?

02:19:43.224 --> 02:19:45.927 position:7% line:83% align:start
LAUGHING MAN: I suppose that's
an ever available choice.

02:19:45.960 --> 02:19:47.862 position:13% line:89% align:start
Anyway, I'm in your debt.

02:19:47.896 --> 02:19:49.331 position:35% line:89% align:start
Thank you.

02:19:49.364 --> 02:19:52.267 position:7% line:83% align:start
The way you kept your promise
was extremely charming.

02:19:57.238 --> 02:20:00.041 position:19% line:83% align:start
TOGUSA: You know what
needs to be done, he said.

02:20:00.075 --> 02:20:02.611 position:19% line:83% align:start
Every Section 9 member
has a unique ability,

02:20:02.645 --> 02:20:04.879 position:7% line:89% align:start
and you work best on your own.

02:20:04.913 --> 02:20:08.517 position:10% line:83% align:start
But individual success is a
reflection of strong team work.

02:20:08.551 --> 02:20:11.454 position:10% line:83% align:start
That was the first nugget of
wisdom the old man offered us

02:20:11.487 --> 02:20:13.589 position:24% line:83% align:start
back in the glory
days of Section 9.

02:20:13.622 --> 02:20:22.565 position:7% line:89% align:start
REPORTER: We've been informed

02:20:22.598 --> 02:20:24.100 position:13% line:89% align:start
will be arriving shortly.

02:20:24.133 --> 02:20:25.668 position:21% line:83% align:start
Throngs of reporters
are gathered here

02:20:25.701 --> 02:20:27.336 position:19% line:83% align:start
in front of the ruling
party headquarters,

02:20:27.370 --> 02:20:29.438 position:10% line:89% align:start
and the atmosphere is tense.

02:20:29.472 --> 02:20:32.274 position:13% line:83% align:start
Making the tabloid rounds
before lower house elections,

02:20:32.308 --> 02:20:35.911 position:13% line:83% align:start
the MHLW scandal involving
Serano Genomics implicated

02:20:35.945 --> 02:20:37.646 position:10% line:89% align:start
Secretary General Yakushima.

02:20:37.681 --> 02:20:39.515 position:19% line:83% align:start
Now, a week after the
forming of a new cabinet,

02:20:39.548 --> 02:20:42.051 position:13% line:83% align:start
this scandal has prompted
a full scale investigation

02:20:42.084 --> 02:20:43.185 position:30% line:83% align:start
by the public
prosecutor's office.

02:20:43.219 --> 02:20:44.588 position:5% line:89% align:start
REPORTER: --said the prosecutor.

02:20:44.621 --> 02:20:46.088 position:13% line:83% align:start
A full scale investigation
has been launched--

02:20:50.159 --> 02:20:51.093 position:24% line:89% align:start
MAN: It's the DA.

02:20:51.127 --> 02:20:52.061 position:33% line:89% align:start
MAN: The DA!

02:20:55.164 --> 02:20:56.298 position:27% line:83% align:start
-Sir, things are
just getting started,

02:20:56.332 --> 02:20:59.068 position:13% line:83% align:start
but before the day's out,
will Yakushima be arrested?

02:20:59.101 --> 02:21:00.370 position:27% line:83% align:start
-What about the
Serano stocks rumored

02:21:00.404 --> 02:21:02.972 position:21% line:83% align:start
to be here at ruling
party headquarters?

02:21:03.005 --> 02:21:05.074 position:7% line:89% align:start
-We have reliable information.

02:21:05.107 --> 02:21:06.676 position:19% line:83% align:start
The Secretary General
would like to be asked

02:21:06.710 --> 02:21:08.278 position:5% line:89% align:start
to come with us for questioning.

02:21:08.311 --> 02:21:10.113 position:16% line:83% align:start
PRESS MEMBER: Any chance
that the cash in sequentially

02:21:10.147 --> 02:21:12.416 position:13% line:83% align:start
numbered bills referred to
in Mr. Serano's testimony

02:21:12.449 --> 02:21:14.351 position:21% line:89% align:start
is being kept here?

02:21:14.384 --> 02:21:17.454 position:21% line:83% align:start
-Everything will be
made clear very shortly.

02:21:17.487 --> 02:21:19.156 position:21% line:83% align:start
My staff and I have
labored long and hard

02:21:19.189 --> 02:21:21.057 position:21% line:83% align:start
to prepare for this
day in anticipation

02:21:21.091 --> 02:21:23.059 position:10% line:89% align:start
of arresting Mr. Yakushima.

02:21:23.093 --> 02:21:24.694 position:21% line:83% align:start
TOGUSA: Is this how
things should be?

02:21:24.728 --> 02:21:27.164 position:19% line:83% align:start
Don't these facts that
Section 9 pieced together

02:21:27.197 --> 02:21:29.065 position:16% line:83% align:start
show the truth about the
Laughing Man incident

02:21:29.099 --> 02:21:31.401 position:21% line:89% align:start
from six years ago?

02:21:31.435 --> 02:21:34.070 position:13% line:83% align:start
And even if the prosecutor
succeeds in uncovering

02:21:34.104 --> 02:21:36.106 position:24% line:83% align:start
the whole scandal,
Yakushima still

02:21:36.139 --> 02:21:38.442 position:27% line:83% align:start
might not resign
from the assembly.

02:21:38.475 --> 02:21:40.544 position:13% line:83% align:start
Exactly how does this make
the world a better place?

02:22:04.034 --> 02:22:08.673 position:5% line:83% align:start
It's not like I had aspirations
to be a hero or anything.

02:22:08.706 --> 02:22:11.609 position:16% line:83% align:start
However, I'm positive we
followed a code of justice

02:22:11.642 --> 02:22:13.511 position:16% line:83% align:start
that all of us believed
in without condition

02:22:13.544 --> 02:22:15.713 position:30% line:89% align:start
or compromise.

02:22:15.746 --> 02:22:18.483 position:16% line:83% align:start
Laughing Man-- you were
the one who first tried

02:22:18.516 --> 02:22:21.118 position:10% line:83% align:start
to shed some light into the
black abyss of this case

02:22:21.152 --> 02:22:23.187 position:21% line:83% align:start
and bring it to the
world's attention.

02:22:23.221 --> 02:22:26.090 position:30% line:83% align:start
Is it possible
that at this moment

02:22:26.123 --> 02:22:29.227 position:5% line:89% align:start
you're feeling the same as I am.

02:22:29.260 --> 02:22:31.162 position:24% line:89% align:start
No, you wouldn't.

02:22:31.195 --> 02:22:32.230 position:30% line:83% align:start
You're not the
type to be bothered

02:22:32.263 --> 02:22:33.799 position:16% line:89% align:start
by something like that.

02:22:33.832 --> 02:22:35.566 position:21% line:83% align:start
You must have had a
revelation about something,

02:22:35.600 --> 02:22:38.135 position:10% line:83% align:start
and you're watching us with
eyes that see the big picture.

02:22:38.169 --> 02:22:40.137 position:24% line:89% align:start
Isn't that right?

02:22:40.171 --> 02:22:42.073 position:33% line:89% align:start
I can tell.

02:22:42.106 --> 02:22:45.577 position:10% line:83% align:start
Major, if all this plays out
the way I think it will--

02:23:11.703 --> 02:23:13.272 position:27% line:89% align:start
BATOU: Hold it.

02:23:13.305 --> 02:23:15.307 position:19% line:83% align:start
Put your hands up nice
and slow and turn around.

02:23:23.850 --> 02:23:25.450 position:27% line:83% align:start
As lousy as you
are, you'd be caught

02:23:25.484 --> 02:23:27.352 position:27% line:83% align:start
before you could
even see Yakushima.

02:23:27.386 --> 02:23:33.258 position:38% line:89% align:start
-Batou.

02:23:33.292 --> 02:23:36.194 position:7% line:89% align:start
You're a dummy, you know that?

02:23:36.228 --> 02:23:36.863 position:24% line:89% align:start
Come on, let's go.

02:23:45.538 --> 02:23:47.439 position:30% line:89% align:start
[car honking]

02:23:55.682 --> 02:23:57.784 position:19% line:89% align:start
-And the star arrives.

02:23:57.817 --> 02:23:59.686 position:16% line:89% align:start
-What took you so long?

02:23:59.719 --> 02:24:01.888 position:27% line:83% align:start
-So where'd you
end up tailing him?

02:24:01.921 --> 02:24:03.121 position:21% line:89% align:start
-Just as we figured.

02:24:03.155 --> 02:24:04.724 position:5% line:89% align:start
He went to the ruling party HQ.

02:24:04.757 --> 02:24:07.560 position:24% line:89% align:start
-Are you serious?

02:24:07.594 --> 02:24:08.328 position:30% line:89% align:start
-What's wrong?

02:24:08.361 --> 02:24:09.295 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hey.

02:24:09.329 --> 02:24:10.730 position:27% line:89% align:start
Are you crying?

02:24:10.763 --> 02:24:11.631 position:33% line:89% align:start
-Yeah, sure.

02:24:11.664 --> 02:24:12.899 position:35% line:89% align:start
Get real.

02:24:12.932 --> 02:24:15.268 position:13% line:83% align:start
-Well, how did everything
go on your end?

02:24:15.301 --> 02:24:17.270 position:30% line:83% align:start
-It seems like
Yakushima's given in.

02:24:17.303 --> 02:24:18.705 position:13% line:89% align:start
He's cooperating with him.

02:24:18.738 --> 02:24:21.341 position:27% line:83% align:start
That's a typical
ex-military fellow for you.

02:24:21.374 --> 02:24:22.843 position:33% line:83% align:start
I'll bet the
prosecution's going to get

02:24:22.876 --> 02:24:24.777 position:24% line:83% align:start
the hero treatment
because of this.

02:24:24.812 --> 02:24:26.446 position:21% line:89% align:start
-You got that right.

02:24:26.479 --> 02:24:28.381 position:7% line:89% align:start
-And you're all OK with this?

02:24:28.414 --> 02:24:30.483 position:10% line:83% align:start
I mean, don't you think the
credit for tracking him down--

02:24:30.516 --> 02:24:32.185 position:27% line:83% align:start
-Should go to us
here at Section 9?

02:24:32.218 --> 02:24:34.621 position:10% line:89% align:start
That's what you want to say?

02:24:34.655 --> 02:24:37.290 position:19% line:83% align:start
Well, it ain't like we
don't feel the same way.

02:24:37.323 --> 02:24:38.859 position:27% line:83% align:start
However, this is
the way the old man

02:24:38.892 --> 02:24:40.426 position:7% line:89% align:start
had it set up the whole time.

02:24:40.460 --> 02:24:41.829 position:13% line:89% align:start
So we're rolling with it.

02:24:41.862 --> 02:24:43.463 position:27% line:89% align:start
TOGUSA: Set up?

02:24:43.497 --> 02:24:45.231 position:41% line:89% align:start
-Yeah.

02:24:45.264 --> 02:24:47.468 position:7% line:83% align:start
When it dawned on the old ape
that the prime minister was

02:24:47.501 --> 02:24:49.837 position:24% line:83% align:start
going to avoid his
secretary general shape up

02:24:49.870 --> 02:24:51.705 position:21% line:83% align:start
before the elections
took place, he

02:24:51.739 --> 02:24:53.440 position:27% line:83% align:start
made a hell of a
bold decision to make

02:24:53.474 --> 02:24:56.276 position:7% line:89% align:start
Section 9 out as the bad guys.

02:24:56.310 --> 02:24:58.746 position:16% line:83% align:start
Right when the major was
disguised as the Laughing Man,

02:24:58.779 --> 02:25:02.216 position:19% line:83% align:start
finagling the truth of
Serano, Section 9's existence

02:25:02.249 --> 02:25:03.050 position:16% line:89% align:start
was leaked to the media.

02:25:03.083 --> 02:25:04.852 position:33% line:83% align:start
That made it
impossible for us to do

02:25:04.885 --> 02:25:07.187 position:5% line:89% align:start
our thing secretly like before.

02:25:07.221 --> 02:25:08.756 position:5% line:89% align:start
So the chief cooked up a scheme.

02:25:08.789 --> 02:25:10.491 position:27% line:83% align:start
He'd make a deal
with the PM and force

02:25:10.524 --> 02:25:12.726 position:16% line:83% align:start
the public prosecutor's
office to take action.

02:25:12.760 --> 02:25:15.362 position:27% line:83% align:start
He pretended to
sacrifice Section 9.

02:25:15.396 --> 02:25:18.666 position:19% line:89% align:start
-Sacrifice Section 9?

02:25:18.699 --> 02:25:21.435 position:24% line:83% align:start
Even if that's the
case, have you any idea

02:25:21.468 --> 02:25:23.303 position:16% line:83% align:start
what it was like for me
these past three months?

02:25:23.337 --> 02:25:25.372 position:10% line:83% align:start
I had no way of knowing what
had happened to you guys?

02:25:25.406 --> 02:25:27.608 position:10% line:89% align:start
-Hey, don't take it so hard.

02:25:27.641 --> 02:25:29.878 position:24% line:83% align:start
Think of it as an
extended vacation.

02:25:29.911 --> 02:25:31.680 position:16% line:83% align:start
-It's not as if we were
filled in on the details

02:25:31.713 --> 02:25:33.715 position:24% line:83% align:start
of this little op
before hand, either.

02:25:33.748 --> 02:25:36.316 position:7% line:83% align:start
-The chief was confident that
we would survive, then find

02:25:36.350 --> 02:25:37.819 position:30% line:83% align:start
each other and
regroup, which is why

02:25:37.852 --> 02:25:41.221 position:13% line:83% align:start
he made the tough decision
to go ahead with his plan.

02:25:41.255 --> 02:25:42.891 position:21% line:83% align:start
-Hell, you're arrest
and confinement

02:25:42.924 --> 02:25:44.324 position:13% line:89% align:start
was a way to protect you.

02:25:44.358 --> 02:25:46.461 position:24% line:83% align:start
The chief had kept
you alive and safe

02:25:46.494 --> 02:25:49.597 position:10% line:83% align:start
by getting you clear of the
Section 9 cleanup operation.

02:25:49.631 --> 02:25:52.467 position:21% line:83% align:start
For one thing, your
body's totally natural.

02:25:52.500 --> 02:25:54.302 position:19% line:83% align:start
And you'd just gotten
out of the hospital, not

02:25:54.335 --> 02:25:56.004 position:27% line:83% align:start
to mention that
you're a married man.

02:25:56.037 --> 02:25:58.773 position:10% line:83% align:start
Fudging data would be hard,
so he kept you out of the loop

02:25:58.807 --> 02:25:59.708 position:24% line:89% align:start
till it was safe.

02:25:59.741 --> 02:26:01.276 position:19% line:89% align:start
Don't be too offended.

02:26:01.309 --> 02:26:03.411 position:27% line:83% align:start
According to the
records, I'm a convict

02:26:03.445 --> 02:26:05.313 position:21% line:83% align:start
spending the rest of
my days up the river.

02:26:05.346 --> 02:26:08.316 position:13% line:83% align:start
-More profit, less honor--
meaning that we're once again

02:26:08.349 --> 02:26:11.020 position:10% line:83% align:start
an offensive organization,
which doesn't officially exist,

02:26:11.053 --> 02:26:12.387 position:35% line:89% align:start
of course.

02:26:12.420 --> 02:26:15.690 position:5% line:89% align:start
-That's what this was all about?

02:26:15.724 --> 02:26:17.492 position:27% line:89% align:start
But-- hey, guys.

02:26:17.525 --> 02:26:18.060 position:35% line:89% align:start
The major.

02:26:18.094 --> 02:26:20.428 position:19% line:89% align:start
What happened to her?

02:26:20.462 --> 02:26:21.396 position:33% line:89% align:start
-Who cares?

02:26:21.429 --> 02:26:23.364 position:21% line:83% align:start
I don't give a rat's
ass about that bitch.

02:26:29.805 --> 02:26:30.840 position:16% line:89% align:start
-Batou, that reminds me.

02:26:30.873 --> 02:26:32.808 position:16% line:83% align:start
Weren't you balling your
eyes out a few months ago?

02:26:32.842 --> 02:26:34.643 position:27% line:89% align:start
-Ah, screw you.

02:26:34.677 --> 02:26:35.510 position:33% line:89% align:start
-Oh, really?

02:26:35.543 --> 02:26:36.912 position:24% line:83% align:start
In that case, what
do you say I grab

02:26:36.946 --> 02:26:38.581 position:19% line:83% align:start
the satellite footage
from the scene?

02:26:38.614 --> 02:26:39.582 position:33% line:89% align:start
SAITO: Yeah.

02:26:39.615 --> 02:26:40.816 position:19% line:83% align:start
And you ought to send
it to the major, too.

02:26:40.850 --> 02:26:41.917 position:33% line:83% align:start
-All right.
Cut it out.

02:26:41.951 --> 02:26:43.451 position:38% line:89% align:start
-Motoko!

02:26:43.486 --> 02:26:43.986 position:41% line:89% align:start
Right?

02:26:44.019 --> 02:26:44.920 position:21% line:89% align:start
BATOU: You bastard.

02:26:44.954 --> 02:26:47.523 position:10% line:89% align:start
I told you to stop, dammit.

02:26:47.556 --> 02:26:50.559 position:27% line:83% align:start
Say good night.
ISHIKAWA: I give, I give!

02:26:55.898 --> 02:26:57.433 position:19% line:89% align:start
-Seems like it's over.

02:27:00.503 --> 02:27:02.738 position:16% line:83% align:start
The rest can be left to
the attorney general.

02:27:02.772 --> 02:27:05.341 position:19% line:89% align:start
My work here is done.

02:27:05.374 --> 02:27:06.776 position:33% line:83% align:start
-The public
prosecutor's office will

02:27:06.809 --> 02:27:09.345 position:19% line:83% align:start
be able to hold their
heads high thanks to this.

02:27:09.378 --> 02:27:11.747 position:10% line:83% align:start
But now that it's all behind
us, what remains for you?

02:27:11.781 --> 02:27:14.050 position:24% line:83% align:start
-For my part, I'm
just gratified that I

02:27:14.084 --> 02:27:16.086 position:5% line:89% align:start
was able to see justice served.

02:27:16.119 --> 02:27:18.354 position:13% line:89% align:start
And that's enough for me.

02:27:18.387 --> 02:27:20.689 position:44% line:89% align:start
-Hm.

02:27:20.723 --> 02:27:23.726 position:5% line:89% align:start
So what are your current plans?

02:27:23.759 --> 02:27:26.662 position:7% line:83% align:start
You can't keep on playing war
with tanks and weapons forever,

02:27:26.695 --> 02:27:28.464 position:35% line:89% align:start
you know?

02:27:28.497 --> 02:27:31.400 position:16% line:89% align:start
Why not join up with us?

02:27:31.433 --> 02:27:32.535 position:21% line:83% align:start
I've always thought
you were better

02:27:32.568 --> 02:27:34.638 position:7% line:89% align:start
suited for the judicial world.

02:27:34.671 --> 02:27:36.940 position:16% line:89% align:start
-Well, I'm not so sure.

02:27:36.973 --> 02:27:39.976 position:13% line:83% align:start
Section 9 wasn't finished
by this trivial matter.

02:27:40.010 --> 02:27:42.646 position:10% line:89% align:start
I intend to rebuild my unit.

02:27:42.679 --> 02:27:45.615 position:13% line:83% align:start
In fact, I'm on my way to
scout a prospective member.

02:27:45.649 --> 02:27:46.516 position:44% line:89% align:start
-Oh.

02:28:23.054 --> 02:28:23.720 position:16% line:89% align:start
KUSANAGI: Now I get it.

02:28:26.724 --> 02:28:28.693 position:19% line:83% align:start
You really aren't the
Laughing Man, that's for sure.

02:29:11.169 --> 02:29:12.670 position:19% line:89% align:start
LAUGHING MAN: Welcome.

02:29:12.703 --> 02:29:14.705 position:5% line:89% align:start
You took longer than I expected.

02:29:14.739 --> 02:29:16.841 position:7% line:89% align:start
KUSANAGI: Don't give me that.

02:29:16.875 --> 02:29:18.809 position:21% line:83% align:start
You didn't even send
me an invitation.

02:29:18.844 --> 02:29:21.679 position:10% line:83% align:start
If you stay right where you
are, eventually the world

02:29:21.712 --> 02:29:22.948 position:24% line:89% align:start
will come to you.

02:29:22.981 --> 02:29:25.650 position:24% line:83% align:start
-I believe it was
Doisneau who said that?

02:29:25.683 --> 02:29:26.584 position:41% line:89% align:start
-Yes.

02:29:26.617 --> 02:29:28.220 position:21% line:83% align:start
-I had a lot of time
to think about what

02:29:28.253 --> 02:29:29.955 position:16% line:89% align:start
should be done with you.

02:29:29.988 --> 02:29:32.157 position:10% line:83% align:start
There wasn't much else to do
while I was floating around.

02:29:32.190 --> 02:29:33.859 position:19% line:83% align:start
-Speaking of which, I
thought you might have

02:29:33.892 --> 02:29:35.994 position:24% line:83% align:start
decided to keep on
floating like that.

02:29:36.028 --> 02:29:37.663 position:19% line:83% align:start
I was afraid that you
were going to die.

02:29:37.696 --> 02:29:40.132 position:13% line:83% align:start
KUSANAGI: I'm not ready to
bid life farewell just yet,

02:29:40.165 --> 02:29:42.734 position:5% line:83% align:start
though I did have an interesting
little near death experience

02:29:42.768 --> 02:29:45.203 position:24% line:83% align:start
during this recent
business when my fully

02:29:45.237 --> 02:29:47.873 position:5% line:89% align:start
remote cyberbrain was blown off.

02:29:47.906 --> 02:29:49.775 position:27% line:83% align:start
-Your brand new
body was destroyed.

02:29:49.808 --> 02:29:51.743 position:13% line:83% align:start
But you still haven't done
a prosthetic swap out.

02:29:56.114 --> 02:29:57.716 position:27% line:83% align:start
KUSANAGI: You've
got a sharp eye.

02:29:57.749 --> 02:30:00.186 position:10% line:89% align:start
-Well, peeking is my hobby.

02:30:00.219 --> 02:30:02.020 position:21% line:89% align:start
-So what's the deal?

02:30:02.054 --> 02:30:04.556 position:19% line:89% align:start
Meaning, what is this?

02:30:04.589 --> 02:30:06.591 position:33% line:83% align:start
Some kind of
information graveyard?

02:30:06.625 --> 02:30:08.127 position:24% line:83% align:start
Did you seriously
think you could

02:30:08.161 --> 02:30:10.829 position:24% line:83% align:start
somehow change the
world from here?

02:30:10.862 --> 02:30:14.133 position:16% line:89% align:start
-Yeah, sort of at first.

02:30:14.167 --> 02:30:16.002 position:7% line:89% align:start
-How do you feel about it now?

02:30:16.035 --> 02:30:19.638 position:19% line:83% align:start
-I'm not blazing with
satisfaction or anything.

02:30:19.671 --> 02:30:21.673 position:27% line:83% align:start
But the truth is
it all ended for me

02:30:21.707 --> 02:30:23.276 position:21% line:83% align:start
the instant I shared
my memories with you.

02:30:23.309 --> 02:30:26.112 position:5% line:89% align:start
At that point, my work was done.

02:30:26.145 --> 02:30:28.881 position:5% line:83% align:start
I figured that you'd probably be
able to run with it from there.

02:30:28.915 --> 02:30:30.183 position:33% line:89% align:start
-Is that so?

02:30:30.216 --> 02:30:32.151 position:7% line:89% align:start
You're a hell of a liar, kid.

02:30:32.185 --> 02:30:34.854 position:21% line:83% align:start
I clearly recall you
didn't want me involved.

02:30:34.887 --> 02:30:35.822 position:33% line:89% align:start
-I'm sorry.

02:30:35.855 --> 02:30:37.790 position:24% line:83% align:start
But the minute you
share and synchronize

02:30:37.824 --> 02:30:40.293 position:19% line:83% align:start
all your information,
you lose your uniqueness

02:30:40.326 --> 02:30:41.961 position:21% line:83% align:start
and become absorbed
into the unconscious

02:30:41.995 --> 02:30:45.598 position:10% line:83% align:start
malice of a third party that
has no motive, or perhaps

02:30:45.631 --> 02:30:49.969 position:16% line:83% align:start
into the will of someone
who does have one.

02:30:50.003 --> 02:30:52.205 position:7% line:83% align:start
-Are those your words based on
what you've acquired from hard

02:30:52.239 --> 02:30:53.639 position:24% line:89% align:start
earned experience?

02:30:53.673 --> 02:30:56.542 position:24% line:83% align:start
-Yes, because the
fact is you yourself

02:30:56.576 --> 02:30:59.012 position:21% line:83% align:start
played the role of a
Laughing Man copycat as well.

02:30:59.045 --> 02:31:02.582 position:13% line:83% align:start
-Well, I have to admit, it
was a fascinating phenomenon.

02:31:02.615 --> 02:31:04.550 position:19% line:83% align:start
At any rate, what was
your underlying reason

02:31:04.584 --> 02:31:07.854 position:7% line:83% align:start
for orchestrating such a huge
event in the first place?

02:31:07.887 --> 02:31:09.856 position:13% line:83% align:start
-To you, everything that's
happening in the world

02:31:09.889 --> 02:31:13.826 position:7% line:83% align:start
appears phony, to be something
other than what it is, right?

02:31:13.860 --> 02:31:15.728 position:30% line:83% align:start
-JD Salinger?
-Yes.

02:31:18.598 --> 02:31:20.633 position:24% line:83% align:start
And when it comes
to cyberization,

02:31:20.666 --> 02:31:23.137 position:21% line:83% align:start
I'm pretty much the
perfect poster boy.

02:31:23.170 --> 02:31:24.805 position:24% line:83% align:start
So you'd think at
the very least,

02:31:24.838 --> 02:31:26.106 position:24% line:83% align:start
I would have felt
terrified of the thought

02:31:26.140 --> 02:31:29.209 position:30% line:83% align:start
of contracting
cyberbrain sclerosis.

02:31:29.243 --> 02:31:30.978 position:30% line:89% align:start
I'll tell you.

02:31:31.011 --> 02:31:32.946 position:16% line:83% align:start
It was a simple piece of
mail I stumbled across

02:31:32.980 --> 02:31:34.681 position:19% line:83% align:start
in the net that began
this whole thing.

02:31:37.217 --> 02:31:39.153 position:24% line:83% align:start
What I'd found was
a blackmail document

02:31:39.186 --> 02:31:42.856 position:19% line:83% align:start
that had probably been
sent to Serano Gemonics.

02:31:42.890 --> 02:31:44.925 position:13% line:83% align:start
It was armed with a thesis
that was a comparative study

02:31:44.958 --> 02:31:47.728 position:21% line:83% align:start
of the inadequacy of
Serrano micro machines

02:31:47.761 --> 02:31:50.931 position:16% line:83% align:start
versus the effectiveness
of the Murai vaccine.

02:31:50.964 --> 02:31:54.335 position:5% line:83% align:start
-Then the original Laughing Man
was the person who authored it?

02:31:54.369 --> 02:31:56.703 position:5% line:89% align:start
-You could say that, I suppose.

02:31:56.737 --> 02:31:58.739 position:19% line:83% align:start
I am the machine that
reveals the world

02:31:58.772 --> 02:32:00.774 position:24% line:83% align:start
to as only I alone
am able to see it.

02:32:00.808 --> 02:32:02.143 position:30% line:89% align:start
-Dziga Vertov.

02:32:02.177 --> 02:32:03.977 position:27% line:83% align:start
He was a Russian
filmmaker, wasn't he?

02:32:04.011 --> 02:32:05.180 position:24% line:89% align:start
LAUGHING MAN: Yes.

02:32:05.213 --> 02:32:07.748 position:5% line:83% align:start
I was kidding myself by thinking
it was my personal mission

02:32:07.781 --> 02:32:09.951 position:19% line:83% align:start
to prove and circulate
that information--

02:32:09.984 --> 02:32:12.153 position:24% line:83% align:start
Vital data I alone
had discovered.

02:32:12.187 --> 02:32:14.621 position:16% line:89% align:start
-Failing spectacularly.

02:32:14.655 --> 02:32:17.691 position:5% line:83% align:start
The pure innocent mediator grew
dejected at the base nature

02:32:17.724 --> 02:32:19.127 position:19% line:83% align:start
of the social system,
and he turned mute.

02:32:19.160 --> 02:32:20.862 position:44% line:89% align:start
Yes.

02:32:20.895 --> 02:32:23.865 position:16% line:83% align:start
It was because of that I
became the vanishing mediator,

02:32:23.898 --> 02:32:26.668 position:13% line:83% align:start
just like an author whose
existence is emphasized

02:32:26.701 --> 02:32:28.069 position:27% line:83% align:start
by the fact that
he rarely puts out

02:32:28.103 --> 02:32:30.405 position:7% line:89% align:start
any new works for publication.

02:32:30.438 --> 02:32:32.107 position:24% line:83% align:start
In other words, by
disappearing, it

02:32:32.140 --> 02:32:34.242 position:21% line:83% align:start
acts as a regulating
medium for the dynamism

02:32:34.275 --> 02:32:35.710 position:19% line:89% align:start
of the social system.

02:32:35.743 --> 02:32:38.113 position:27% line:83% align:start
Per sociological
theory, it ultimately

02:32:38.146 --> 02:32:40.148 position:21% line:83% align:start
vanishes, leaving no
trace of its presence,

02:32:40.181 --> 02:32:42.317 position:7% line:89% align:start
inside or outside the system.

02:32:42.350 --> 02:32:44.953 position:10% line:83% align:start
-Fredric Jameson, I believe.
-Yes.

02:32:44.986 --> 02:32:46.788 position:38% line:89% align:start
But no.

02:32:46.821 --> 02:32:48.857 position:7% line:89% align:start
The latter was Masachi Osawa.

02:32:48.890 --> 02:32:51.059 position:24% line:83% align:start
Even though I was
familiar with the words,

02:32:51.092 --> 02:32:53.761 position:13% line:83% align:start
I didn't believe it until
I saw it with my own eyes.

02:32:53.795 --> 02:32:55.730 position:21% line:83% align:start
Who knew that copies
could still be produced

02:32:55.763 --> 02:32:58.200 position:21% line:83% align:start
despite the absence
of an original?

02:32:58.234 --> 02:33:00.236 position:21% line:83% align:start
If you had to give a
name to this phenomenon,

02:33:00.269 --> 02:33:02.670 position:16% line:89% align:start
what would you label it?

02:33:02.704 --> 02:33:04.973 position:24% line:83% align:start
-It would be stand
alone complex.

02:33:05.007 --> 02:33:06.242 position:38% line:83% align:start
-Right.
Yes.

02:33:06.275 --> 02:33:08.210 position:16% line:89% align:start
The stand alone complex.

02:33:08.244 --> 02:33:11.013 position:5% line:83% align:start
From the start, the very nature
of our current social system

02:33:11.046 --> 02:33:13.015 position:24% line:83% align:start
has contained the
mechanisms to trigger

02:33:13.048 --> 02:33:15.117 position:10% line:89% align:start
such an amazing occurrence.

02:33:15.151 --> 02:33:16.919 position:21% line:83% align:start
Personally, however,
I feel this marks

02:33:16.952 --> 02:33:19.188 position:24% line:83% align:start
the beginning of a
new era of despair.

02:33:19.221 --> 02:33:20.923 position:21% line:89% align:start
What's your opinion?

02:33:20.956 --> 02:33:21.624 position:30% line:89% align:start
-I don't know.

02:33:21.656 --> 02:33:24.894 position:7% line:89% align:start
It's impossible for me to say.

02:33:24.927 --> 02:33:27.096 position:13% line:83% align:start
Although I have found one
thing capable of restoring

02:33:27.129 --> 02:33:29.298 position:16% line:83% align:start
your individuality after
all your information

02:33:29.331 --> 02:33:31.100 position:19% line:89% align:start
has been synchronized.

02:33:31.133 --> 02:33:31.800 position:33% line:89% align:start
-Oh, really?

02:33:31.834 --> 02:33:32.735 position:27% line:89% align:start
And what's that?

02:33:37.773 --> 02:33:40.075 position:21% line:83% align:start
KUSANAGI: Every day
human curiosity.

02:33:40.109 --> 02:33:41.076 position:44% line:89% align:start
-Oh.

02:33:41.110 --> 02:33:42.211 position:30% line:89% align:start
You're right.

02:33:42.244 --> 02:33:45.047 position:13% line:83% align:start
You know, that's something
that never occurred to me.

02:33:45.080 --> 02:33:49.118 position:21% line:83% align:start
I think my brain has
already started to harden.

02:33:49.151 --> 02:33:49.919 position:44% line:89% align:start
OK.

02:33:49.952 --> 02:33:50.986 position:27% line:83% align:start
What's going to
happen to me now?

02:33:51.020 --> 02:33:53.889 position:19% line:83% align:start
Will I be arrested for
kidnapping or for inciting

02:33:53.923 --> 02:33:56.359 position:19% line:83% align:start
multiple simultaneous
terrorist attacks?

02:33:56.393 --> 02:33:58.161 position:21% line:89% align:start
-Hey, don't ask me.

02:33:58.195 --> 02:34:01.264 position:19% line:83% align:start
That little matter is
completely at his discretion.

02:34:01.298 --> 02:34:04.267 position:13% line:89% align:start
Why not ask him yourself?

02:34:04.301 --> 02:34:06.802 position:21% line:83% align:start
-I've been listening
in for a while now.

02:34:06.835 --> 02:34:08.505 position:30% line:83% align:start
But without an
external memory device,

02:34:08.538 --> 02:34:11.141 position:5% line:89% align:start
I couldn't keep up with you two.

02:34:11.174 --> 02:34:13.944 position:19% line:83% align:start
Have you every single
book in here, young man?

02:34:13.977 --> 02:34:15.912 position:27% line:89% align:start
-Not every book.

02:34:15.946 --> 02:34:17.347 position:19% line:89% align:start
-Let me introduce you.

02:34:17.380 --> 02:34:19.015 position:16% line:89% align:start
This is Daisuke Aramaki.

02:34:19.049 --> 02:34:21.818 position:24% line:83% align:start
He's my boss, the
chief of Section 9.

02:34:21.851 --> 02:34:24.788 position:7% line:89% align:start
-I'm very pleased to meet you.

02:34:24.821 --> 02:34:26.223 position:27% line:83% align:start
-Do you actually
plan to continue

02:34:26.256 --> 02:34:28.992 position:13% line:83% align:start
with this dull, futureless
occupation of preserving

02:34:29.025 --> 02:34:31.494 position:13% line:83% align:start
obsolete printed materials
that nowadays are only

02:34:31.529 --> 02:34:33.797 position:5% line:89% align:start
published out of force of habit?

02:34:33.830 --> 02:34:34.498 position:41% line:89% align:start
-Yes.

02:34:34.532 --> 02:34:36.500 position:5% line:89% align:start
If I'm allowed to, then I will.

02:34:36.534 --> 02:34:38.335 position:24% line:83% align:start
ARAMAKI: As far as
this case is concerned,

02:34:38.368 --> 02:34:40.870 position:10% line:83% align:start
it'll probably be concluded
that the original Laughing

02:34:40.904 --> 02:34:43.441 position:7% line:89% align:start
Man never officially existed.

02:34:43.474 --> 02:34:45.141 position:10% line:89% align:start
So I have an offer to make.

02:34:45.175 --> 02:34:46.344 position:30% line:89% align:start
And it's this.

02:34:46.377 --> 02:34:49.247 position:7% line:83% align:start
Do you want to put your hacker
skills to use and join up

02:34:49.280 --> 02:34:51.482 position:19% line:83% align:start
with Section 9 as our
ninth regular team player?

02:34:54.318 --> 02:34:55.219 position:41% line:89% align:start
-Wow.

02:34:55.253 --> 02:34:56.220 position:30% line:89% align:start
I'm surprised.

02:34:56.254 --> 02:34:58.356 position:10% line:89% align:start
You came here to recruit me.

02:34:58.389 --> 02:34:59.923 position:30% line:89% align:start
-That's right.

02:34:59.956 --> 02:35:00.790 position:41% line:89% align:start
-Man.

02:35:00.824 --> 02:35:02.460 position:27% line:89% align:start
I'm speechless.

02:35:02.493 --> 02:35:05.296 position:19% line:83% align:start
It does sound like it
would be interesting.

02:35:05.329 --> 02:35:09.066 position:10% line:83% align:start
But I'm gonna have to pass,
because as much as I hate

02:35:09.100 --> 02:35:10.501 position:30% line:83% align:start
to say it, I'm
not a team player.

02:35:20.244 --> 02:35:22.013 position:7% line:89% align:start
-Well, the kid shot you down.

02:35:22.046 --> 02:35:23.080 position:35% line:89% align:start
Now what?

02:35:23.114 --> 02:35:25.016 position:27% line:89% align:start
-Another thing.

02:35:25.049 --> 02:35:27.885 position:13% line:83% align:start
Section 9 will resume work
as an anti crime unit.

02:35:27.918 --> 02:35:31.389 position:10% line:83% align:start
It'll remain that way for as
long as you and I want it to.

02:35:31.422 --> 02:35:32.323 position:24% line:89% align:start
That's all, Major.

02:35:55.247 --> 02:35:59.850 position:16% line:83% align:start
Major, assemble the team
with an A2 load out.

02:35:59.884 --> 02:36:00.918 position:5% line:89% align:start
KUSANAGI: Batou, you copy that?

02:36:04.889 --> 02:36:05.856 position:16% line:89% align:start
BATOU: You need a lift?

02:36:08.627 --> 02:36:11.563 position:24% line:89% align:start
KUSANAGI: Togusa.

02:36:11.596 --> 02:36:13.532 position:7% line:89% align:start
TOGUSA: I'm already on my way.

02:36:13.565 --> 02:36:14.299 position:21% line:89% align:start
KUSANAGI: Ishikawa.

02:36:14.333 --> 02:36:15.901 position:41% line:89% align:start
Saito.

02:36:15.934 --> 02:36:17.002 position:13% line:83% align:start
SAITO: I'll go separately
and meet up with you.

02:36:21.239 --> 02:36:24.176 position:13% line:89% align:start
ISHIKAWA: Ready on my end.

02:36:24.209 --> 02:36:25.043 position:33% line:89% align:start
BATOU: Pazu.

02:36:25.077 --> 02:36:26.044 position:41% line:89% align:start
Borma.

02:36:26.078 --> 02:36:27.512 position:13% line:89% align:start
